INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bank-finance-budgeting-1','finance','finance:budgeting','finance-budgeting-1','beginner','mcq','What is the main purpose of a personal budget?','What is the main purpose of a personal budget?',ARRAY['To plan how your income is allocated to spending and saving','To guarantee your investments earn a higher return','To remove the need to ever track your expenses again','To increase your credit limit with lenders']::text[],ARRAY['To plan how your income is allocated to spending and saving','To guarantee your investments earn a higher return','To remove the need to ever track your expenses again','To increase your credit limit with lenders']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'A budget is a plan that maps your income against your spending and saving so you can direct your money intentionally.','A budget is a plan that maps your income against your spending and saving so you can direct your money intentionally.','A budget is simply a plan for where your money goes over a period, usually a month. It helps you make sure essential needs are covered, debts are paid, and some money is set aside for goals before discretionary spending. Reviewing it regularly lets you spot overspending early and adjust before it becomes a problem.','A budget is simply a plan for where your money goes over a period, usually a month. It helps you make sure essential needs are covered, debts are paid, and some money is set aside for goals before discretionary spending. Reviewing it regularly lets you spot overspending early and adjust before it becomes a problem.',10,'approved','curated-taste');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bank-finance-budgeting-2','finance','finance:budgeting','finance-budgeting-2','intermediate','mcq','In the popular 50/30/20 budgeting guideline, what does the 20% portion represent?','In the popular 50/30/20 budgeting guideline, what does the 20% portion represent?',ARRAY['Savings and debt repayment beyond minimums','Rent and other housing costs','Discretionary ''wants'' like dining out','Taxes withheld from your paycheck']::text[],ARRAY['Savings and debt repayment beyond minimums','Rent and other housing costs','Discretionary ''wants'' like dining out','Taxes withheld from your paycheck']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Under the 50/30/20 guideline, 50% goes to needs, 30% to wants, and 20% to savings and extra debt repayment.','Under the 50/30/20 guideline, 50% goes to needs, 30% to wants, and 20% to savings and extra debt repayment.','The 50/30/20 rule is a simple framework that splits after-tax income into three buckets: needs, wants, and savings or debt paydown. It is meant as a starting point rather than a strict law, and the percentages can be adjusted to fit your situation. Its value is in forcing you to consciously reserve a slice for your future rather than spending everything you earn.','The 50/30/20 rule is a simple framework that splits after-tax income into three buckets: needs, wants, and savings or debt paydown. It is meant as a starting point rather than a strict law, and the percentages can be adjusted to fit your situation. Its value is in forcing you to consciously reserve a slice for your future rather than spending everything you earn.',15,'approved','curated-taste');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bank-finance-budgeting-3','finance','finance:budgeting','finance-budgeting-3','advanced','mcq','A common guideline suggests an emergency fund should cover roughly how much of your living expenses?','A common guideline suggests an emergency fund should cover roughly how much of your living expenses?',ARRAY['Three to six months of essential expenses','One week of expenses','Two full years of expenses','Exactly one month''s rent']::text[],ARRAY['Three to six months of essential expenses','One week of expenses','Two full years of expenses','Exactly one month''s rent']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Most guidance recommends keeping three to six months of essential living costs in an accessible emergency fund to cover income loss or surprise bills.','Most guidance recommends keeping three to six months of essential living costs in an accessible emergency fund to cover income loss or surprise bills.','An emergency fund is cash set aside specifically for unexpected events like job loss, medical bills, or urgent repairs. Holding three to six months of essential expenses is a common target, with people in less stable jobs leaning toward the higher end. Because the point is quick access without loss of value, this money is usually kept in a safe, liquid account rather than invested in volatile assets.','An emergency fund is cash set aside specifically for unexpected events like job loss, medical bills, or urgent repairs. Holding three to six months of essential expenses is a common target, with people in less stable jobs leaning toward the higher end. Because the point is quick access without loss of value, this money is usually kept in a safe, liquid account rather than invested in volatile assets.',25,'approved','curated-taste');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bank-finance-credit-1','finance','finance:credit','finance-credit-1','beginner','truefalse','Paying your credit card balance in full and on time each month generally helps build a positive credit history.','Paying your credit card balance in full and on time each month generally helps build a positive credit history.',ARRAY['True','False']::text[],ARRAY['True','False']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Consistent, on-time payments are one of the strongest positive signals in a credit history, and paying in full also avoids interest charges.','Consistent, on-time payments are one of the strongest positive signals in a credit history, and paying in full also avoids interest charges.','Payment history is typically the single most important factor in a credit score. Paying at least the minimum on time avoids late marks, but paying the full statement balance also means you avoid interest entirely. Over time, a record of reliable payments demonstrates to lenders that you are a low-risk borrower.','Payment history is typically the single most important factor in a credit score. Paying at least the minimum on time avoids late marks, but paying the full statement balance also means you avoid interest entirely. Over time, a record of reliable payments demonstrates to lenders that you are a low-risk borrower.',10,'approved','curated-taste');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bank-finance-credit-2','finance','finance:credit','finance-credit-2','intermediate','mcq','Credit utilization, an important factor in many credit scores, measures what?','Credit utilization, an important factor in many credit scores, measures what?',ARRAY['The share of your available revolving credit that you are currently using','The total number of years your oldest account has been open','How many different lenders have ever checked your credit','The interest rate charged on your largest loan']::text[],ARRAY['The share of your available revolving credit that you are currently using','The total number of years your oldest account has been open','How many different lenders have ever checked your credit','The interest rate charged on your largest loan']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Credit utilization is the ratio of your current revolving balances to your total available credit limits.','Credit utilization is the ratio of your current revolving balances to your total available credit limits.','Credit utilization compares how much revolving credit you are using to how much you have available, expressed as a percentage. Lower utilization generally signals that you are not overly reliant on borrowed money, which tends to support a higher score. A common rule of thumb is to keep utilization well below 30%, and paying balances down before the statement closes can help.','Credit utilization compares how much revolving credit you are using to how much you have available, expressed as a percentage. Lower utilization generally signals that you are not overly reliant on borrowed money, which tends to support a higher score. A common rule of thumb is to keep utilization well below 30%, and paying balances down before the statement closes can help.',15,'approved','curated-taste');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bank-finance-credit-3','finance','finance:credit','finance-credit-3','advanced','mcq','When tackling several debts, what distinguishes the ''debt avalanche'' method from the ''debt snowball'' method?','When tackling several debts, what distinguishes the ''debt avalanche'' method from the ''debt snowball'' method?',ARRAY['The avalanche targets the highest interest rate first, while the snowball targets the smallest balance first','The avalanche targets the smallest balance first, while the snowball targets the highest rate first','The avalanche pays only minimums while the snowball skips minimums','Both methods always pay the largest balance first']::text[],ARRAY['The avalanche targets the highest interest rate first, while the snowball targets the smallest balance first','The avalanche targets the smallest balance first, while the snowball targets the highest rate first','The avalanche pays only minimums while the snowball skips minimums','Both methods always pay the largest balance first']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'The avalanche prioritizes the highest interest rate to minimize total interest, while the snowball prioritizes the smallest balance to build motivation through quick wins.','The avalanche prioritizes the highest interest rate to minimize total interest, while the snowball prioritizes the smallest balance to build motivation through quick wins.','Both strategies have you pay minimums on every debt and then put extra money toward one target debt. The avalanche method attacks the highest interest rate first, which mathematically minimizes the total interest you pay. The snowball method attacks the smallest balance first, producing faster psychological wins that can help people stay motivated even if it costs slightly more in interest.','Both strategies have you pay minimums on every debt and then put extra money toward one target debt. The avalanche method attacks the highest interest rate first, which mathematically minimizes the total interest you pay. The snowball method attacks the smallest balance first, producing faster psychological wins that can help people stay motivated even if it costs slightly more in interest.',25,'approved','curated-taste');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bank-finance-investing-1','finance','finance:investing','finance-investing-1','beginner','mcq','What does it mean to diversify an investment portfolio?','What does it mean to diversify an investment portfolio?',ARRAY['Spreading money across many different investments to reduce risk','Putting all your money into a single promising company','Only investing during years when markets are rising','Borrowing money to increase the size of your bets']::text[],ARRAY['Spreading money across many different investments to reduce risk','Putting all your money into a single promising company','Only investing during years when markets are rising','Borrowing money to increase the size of your bets']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Diversification spreads your money across many assets so that a poor result from any one of them has a smaller impact on the whole.','Diversification spreads your money across many assets so that a poor result from any one of them has a smaller impact on the whole.','Diversification is the practice of holding a variety of investments rather than concentrating in one place. Because different assets often do not move in lockstep, a loss in one can be offset by gains or stability in others, smoothing overall results. It does not eliminate risk, but it reduces the chance that a single bad outcome devastates your portfolio.','Diversification is the practice of holding a variety of investments rather than concentrating in one place. Because different assets often do not move in lockstep, a loss in one can be offset by gains or stability in others, smoothing overall results. It does not eliminate risk, but it reduces the chance that a single bad outcome devastates your portfolio.',10,'approved','curated-taste');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bank-finance-investing-2','finance','finance:investing','finance-investing-2','intermediate','mcq','A broad-market index fund is generally designed to do what?','A broad-market index fund is generally designed to do what?',ARRAY['Track the performance of a whole market index at low cost','Beat the market by frequently picking individual winning stocks','Guarantee a fixed return regardless of market conditions','Hold only a single company''s stock for maximum focus']::text[],ARRAY['Track the performance of a whole market index at low cost','Beat the market by frequently picking individual winning stocks','Guarantee a fixed return regardless of market conditions','Hold only a single company''s stock for maximum focus']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'An index fund aims to match, not beat, the returns of a market index by holding its components, which keeps costs low.','An index fund aims to match, not beat, the returns of a market index by holding its components, which keeps costs low.','An index fund passively holds the securities in a target index, such as a broad stock market index, rather than trying to outsmart the market. Because it requires little active management, it typically charges very low fees, which directly improves long-term net returns. This combination of instant diversification and low cost is why index funds are a popular core holding for long-term investors.','An index fund passively holds the securities in a target index, such as a broad stock market index, rather than trying to outsmart the market. Because it requires little active management, it typically charges very low fees, which directly improves long-term net returns. This combination of instant diversification and low cost is why index funds are a popular core holding for long-term investors.',15,'approved','curated-taste');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bank-finance-investing-3','finance','finance:investing','finance-investing-3','advanced','mcq','Why does compound growth tend to favor investors who start early, even with smaller contributions?','Why does compound growth tend to favor investors who start early, even with smaller contributions?',ARRAY['Earnings are reinvested and themselves generate earnings over a longer time horizon','Starting early guarantees a higher interest rate than starting later','Early investments are exempt from any market losses','Compounding only applies to money invested before a certain age']::text[],ARRAY['Earnings are reinvested and themselves generate earnings over a longer time horizon','Starting early guarantees a higher interest rate than starting later','Early investments are exempt from any market losses','Compounding only applies to money invested before a certain age']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Compounding reinvests returns so they generate further returns, and a longer time horizon gives that snowball effect far more time to grow.','Compounding reinvests returns so they generate further returns, and a longer time horizon gives that snowball effect far more time to grow.','Compound growth means the returns you earn are reinvested and go on to earn returns of their own. The longer your money stays invested, the more dramatic this snowball becomes, so time in the market is often more powerful than the amount invested. This is why a modest sum invested in your twenties can outgrow a larger sum invested decades later.','Compound growth means the returns you earn are reinvested and go on to earn returns of their own. The longer your money stays invested, the more dramatic this snowball becomes, so time in the market is often more powerful than the amount invested. This is why a modest sum invested in your twenties can outgrow a larger sum invested decades later.',25,'approved','curated-taste');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bank-finance-retirement-1','finance','finance:retirement','finance-retirement-1','beginner','mcq','What is the main advantage of a tax-advantaged retirement account compared with an ordinary taxable account?','What is the main advantage of a tax-advantaged retirement account compared with an ordinary taxable account?',ARRAY['It offers tax benefits designed to encourage long-term retirement saving','It guarantees your investments can never lose value','It lets you withdraw money any time with no rules at all','It pays a fixed government-set interest rate every year']::text[],ARRAY['It offers tax benefits designed to encourage long-term retirement saving','It guarantees your investments can never lose value','It lets you withdraw money any time with no rules at all','It pays a fixed government-set interest rate every year']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Tax-advantaged retirement accounts provide tax breaks, such as deferred or tax-free growth, to reward saving for retirement.','Tax-advantaged retirement accounts provide tax breaks, such as deferred or tax-free growth, to reward saving for retirement.','Tax-advantaged retirement accounts give you a tax incentive to set money aside for the long term. Depending on the account type, you might get a tax break when you contribute or tax-free withdrawals later, and investments inside the account can grow without yearly tax drag. In exchange for these benefits, the accounts usually have rules and penalties that discourage withdrawing the money before retirement.','Tax-advantaged retirement accounts give you a tax incentive to set money aside for the long term. Depending on the account type, you might get a tax break when you contribute or tax-free withdrawals later, and investments inside the account can grow without yearly tax drag. In exchange for these benefits, the accounts usually have rules and penalties that discourage withdrawing the money before retirement.',10,'approved','curated-taste');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bank-finance-retirement-2','finance','finance:retirement','finance-retirement-2','intermediate','mcq','An employer ''match'' on retirement contributions is best described as what?','An employer ''match'' on retirement contributions is best described as what?',ARRAY['Extra money your employer adds based on what you contribute, up to a limit','A loan from your employer that must be repaid with interest','A tax your employer deducts from your retirement savings','A penalty for contributing too much to your account']::text[],ARRAY['Extra money your employer adds based on what you contribute, up to a limit','A loan from your employer that must be repaid with interest','A tax your employer deducts from your retirement savings','A penalty for contributing too much to your account']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'An employer match is additional money the employer contributes in proportion to your own contributions, effectively an immediate return on your savings.','An employer match is additional money the employer contributes in proportion to your own contributions, effectively an immediate return on your savings.','Many employers offer to match a portion of what you contribute to a workplace retirement plan, up to a set percentage of your pay. This match is essentially free money and an immediate boost to your savings, so contributing at least enough to capture the full match is widely considered a priority. Failing to contribute enough means leaving part of your compensation on the table.','Many employers offer to match a portion of what you contribute to a workplace retirement plan, up to a set percentage of your pay. This match is essentially free money and an immediate boost to your savings, so contributing at least enough to capture the full match is widely considered a priority. Failing to contribute enough means leaving part of your compensation on the table.',15,'approved','curated-taste');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bank-finance-retirement-3','finance','finance:retirement','finance-retirement-3','advanced','mcq','What is the key difference between a traditional (pre-tax) and a Roth (after-tax) retirement account?','What is the key difference between a traditional (pre-tax) and a Roth (after-tax) retirement account?',ARRAY['Traditional contributions may be taxed at withdrawal, while qualified Roth withdrawals are tax-free','Roth contributions are always taxed again when you withdraw them','Traditional accounts can never be invested in stocks','Roth accounts require you to pay tax on growth every year']::text[],ARRAY['Traditional contributions may be taxed at withdrawal, while qualified Roth withdrawals are tax-free','Roth contributions are always taxed again when you withdraw them','Traditional accounts can never be invested in stocks','Roth accounts require you to pay tax on growth every year']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Traditional accounts typically defer tax until withdrawal, whereas Roth accounts are funded with after-tax money and allow qualified withdrawals tax-free.','Traditional accounts typically defer tax until withdrawal, whereas Roth accounts are funded with after-tax money and allow qualified withdrawals tax-free.','The core distinction is when you pay tax. Traditional accounts often let you contribute pre-tax money and defer taxes until you withdraw in retirement, while Roth accounts use money you have already been taxed on so that qualified future withdrawals, including growth, are tax-free. Choosing between them often comes down to whether you expect your tax rate to be higher now or in retirement.','The core distinction is when you pay tax. Traditional accounts often let you contribute pre-tax money and defer taxes until you withdraw in retirement, while Roth accounts use money you have already been taxed on so that qualified future withdrawals, including growth, are tax-free. Choosing between them often comes down to whether you expect your tax rate to be higher now or in retirement.',25,'approved','curated-taste');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-finance-budgeting-b-1','finance','finance:budgeting','finance-budgeting-b-1','beginner','mcq','What is the main purpose of a personal budget?','What is the main purpose of a personal budget?',ARRAY['To plan how income is allocated across spending and saving','To guarantee a higher salary each year','To eliminate the need to ever track expenses','To replace the need for a bank account']::text[],ARRAY['To plan how income is allocated across spending and saving','To guarantee a higher salary each year','To eliminate the need to ever track expenses','To replace the need for a bank account']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'A budget is a plan that allocates your income across expenses, savings, and goals.','A budget is a plan that allocates your income across expenses, savings, and goals.','A budget is a forward-looking plan for your money. It assigns every dollar of income to a purpose, such as bills, spending, or saving. Reviewing it regularly helps you spot overspending and stay on track toward goals.','A budget is a forward-looking plan for your money. It assigns every dollar of income to a purpose, such as bills, spending, or saving. Reviewing it regularly helps you spot overspending and stay on track toward goals.',10,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-finance-budgeting-b-2','finance','finance:budgeting','finance-budgeting-b-2','beginner','truefalse','An emergency fund is money set aside to cover unexpected expenses such as car repairs or medical bills.','An emergency fund is money set aside to cover unexpected expenses such as car repairs or medical bills.',ARRAY['True','False']::text[],ARRAY['True','False']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'An emergency fund is savings reserved specifically for unexpected, urgent costs.','An emergency fund is savings reserved specifically for unexpected, urgent costs.','An emergency fund is a cash reserve held in an easily accessible account. It cushions against surprises like job loss or sudden repairs so you avoid borrowing at high interest. A common guideline is to save three to six months of essential expenses.','An emergency fund is a cash reserve held in an easily accessible account. It cushions against surprises like job loss or sudden repairs so you avoid borrowing at high interest. A common guideline is to save three to six months of essential expenses.',10,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-finance-budgeting-i-1','finance','finance:budgeting','finance-budgeting-i-1','intermediate','mcq','In the popular 50/30/20 budgeting guideline, what does the 20% portion represent?','In the popular 50/30/20 budgeting guideline, what does the 20% portion represent?',ARRAY['Savings and debt repayment','Housing costs only','Entertainment and dining out','Taxes withheld from your paycheck']::text[],ARRAY['Savings and debt repayment','Housing costs only','Entertainment and dining out','Taxes withheld from your paycheck']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'In the 50/30/20 guideline, 20% of after-tax income goes to savings and paying down debt.','In the 50/30/20 guideline, 20% of after-tax income goes to savings and paying down debt.','The 50/30/20 rule splits after-tax income into three buckets. Fifty percent covers needs, thirty percent covers wants, and twenty percent goes to savings and extra debt repayment. It is a flexible starting framework, not a rigid rule.','The 50/30/20 rule splits after-tax income into three buckets. Fifty percent covers needs, thirty percent covers wants, and twenty percent goes to savings and extra debt repayment. It is a flexible starting framework, not a rigid rule.',15,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-finance-budgeting-i-2','finance','finance:budgeting','finance-budgeting-i-2','intermediate','mcq','Why is paying yourself first considered an effective saving strategy?','Why is paying yourself first considered an effective saving strategy?',ARRAY['Saving happens automatically before money can be spent','It increases your gross salary','It removes the need for any budget','It guarantees investment returns']::text[],ARRAY['Saving happens automatically before money can be spent','It increases your gross salary','It removes the need for any budget','It guarantees investment returns']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Paying yourself first moves savings out automatically before discretionary spending can consume it.','Paying yourself first moves savings out automatically before discretionary spending can consume it.','Paying yourself first means directing a set amount to savings as soon as you are paid, often through automation. Because the money leaves before you can spend it, saving becomes consistent and effortless. This habit treats savings as a fixed priority rather than leftover money.','Paying yourself first means directing a set amount to savings as soon as you are paid, often through automation. Because the money leaves before you can spend it, saving becomes consistent and effortless. This habit treats savings as a fixed priority rather than leftover money.',15,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-finance-budgeting-a-1','finance','finance:budgeting','finance-budgeting-a-1','advanced','mcq','What distinguishes a zero-based budget from other budgeting methods?','What distinguishes a zero-based budget from other budgeting methods?',ARRAY['Every dollar of income is assigned a specific job until nothing is left unallocated','You must spend down your account to zero each month','It only works for people with no debt','It ignores irregular or variable expenses']::text[],ARRAY['Every dollar of income is assigned a specific job until nothing is left unallocated','You must spend down your account to zero each month','It only works for people with no debt','It ignores irregular or variable expenses']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'In a zero-based budget, income minus all allocations equals zero, so every dollar has an assigned purpose.','In a zero-based budget, income minus all allocations equals zero, so every dollar has an assigned purpose.','Zero-based budgeting gives every dollar a job, including savings and debt payments, until allocations equal income. It does not mean your bank balance hits zero. The method forces deliberate decisions about all income, which improves awareness and reduces aimless spending.','Zero-based budgeting gives every dollar a job, including savings and debt payments, until allocations equal income. It does not mean your bank balance hits zero. The method forces deliberate decisions about all income, which improves awareness and reduces aimless spending.',25,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-finance-budgeting-a-2','finance','finance:budgeting','finance-budgeting-a-2','advanced','mcq','When building a budget around an irregular income, which approach is generally most stable?','When building a budget around an irregular income, which approach is generally most stable?',ARRAY['Base spending on a conservative estimate of your lowest typical monthly income','Base spending on your single highest-earning month','Spend each month''s full income immediately','Avoid saving until income becomes predictable']::text[],ARRAY['Base spending on a conservative estimate of your lowest typical monthly income','Base spending on your single highest-earning month','Spend each month''s full income immediately','Avoid saving until income becomes predictable']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Budgeting from a conservative low-income baseline prevents overcommitting during lean months.','Budgeting from a conservative low-income baseline prevents overcommitting during lean months.','Variable income makes fixed commitments risky if based on good months. Budgeting from a conservative baseline of your lowest typical earnings keeps essential spending sustainable. Surplus from stronger months can then build a buffer that smooths out the lean periods.','Variable income makes fixed commitments risky if based on good months. Budgeting from a conservative baseline of your lowest typical earnings keeps essential spending sustainable. Surplus from stronger months can then build a buffer that smooths out the lean periods.',25,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-finance-credit-b-1','finance','finance:credit','finance-credit-b-1','beginner','mcq','What does a credit score primarily measure?','What does a credit score primarily measure?',ARRAY['How likely you are to repay borrowed money','How much money you currently have in savings','Your total annual income','The value of your home']::text[],ARRAY['How likely you are to repay borrowed money','How much money you currently have in savings','Your total annual income','The value of your home']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'A credit score estimates your creditworthiness, or how likely you are to repay debt.','A credit score estimates your creditworthiness, or how likely you are to repay debt.','A credit score is a number summarizing your credit history. Lenders use it to gauge the risk of lending to you, which affects approval and interest rates. It reflects borrowing behavior, not your income or wealth.','A credit score is a number summarizing your credit history. Lenders use it to gauge the risk of lending to you, which affects approval and interest rates. It reflects borrowing behavior, not your income or wealth.',10,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-finance-credit-b-2','finance','finance:credit','finance-credit-b-2','beginner','truefalse','Paying your credit card bill in full each month lets you avoid interest charges on purchases.','Paying your credit card bill in full each month lets you avoid interest charges on purchases.',ARRAY['True','False']::text[],ARRAY['True','False']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Paying the full statement balance by the due date avoids interest on regular purchases during the grace period.','Paying the full statement balance by the due date avoids interest on regular purchases during the grace period.','Credit cards typically offer a grace period on purchases when you pay the statement balance in full by the due date. Carrying a balance forfeits that grace period and triggers interest charges. Paying in full each month is the cheapest way to use a credit card.','Credit cards typically offer a grace period on purchases when you pay the statement balance in full by the due date. Carrying a balance forfeits that grace period and triggers interest charges. Paying in full each month is the cheapest way to use a credit card.',10,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-finance-credit-i-1','finance','finance:credit','finance-credit-i-1','intermediate','mcq','Credit utilization, an important scoring factor, refers to what?','Credit utilization, an important scoring factor, refers to what?',ARRAY['The share of your available revolving credit that you are currently using','The number of years your oldest account has been open','How many times you check your own credit report','The total amount you have ever borrowed in your life']::text[],ARRAY['The share of your available revolving credit that you are currently using','The number of years your oldest account has been open','How many times you check your own credit report','The total amount you have ever borrowed in your life']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Credit utilization is the ratio of your balances to your available credit limits.','Credit utilization is the ratio of your balances to your available credit limits.','Credit utilization compares how much revolving credit you are using to your total available limits. Lower utilization generally signals less risk and supports a higher score. Keeping balances well below your limits is widely recommended.','Credit utilization compares how much revolving credit you are using to your total available limits. Lower utilization generally signals less risk and supports a higher score. Keeping balances well below your limits is widely recommended.',15,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-finance-credit-i-2','finance','finance:credit','finance-credit-i-2','intermediate','mcq','Which factor typically has the largest influence on a common credit score?','Which factor typically has the largest influence on a common credit score?',ARRAY['Your payment history','Your employer''s name','Your account passwords','The brand of card you carry']::text[],ARRAY['Your payment history','Your employer''s name','Your account passwords','The brand of card you carry']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Payment history, whether you pay on time, is usually the most heavily weighted scoring factor.','Payment history, whether you pay on time, is usually the most heavily weighted scoring factor.','Most scoring models weight payment history most heavily because on-time payment is the strongest signal of reliability. Even one late payment can hurt a score and linger on a report for years. Consistently paying on time is the single best way to build credit.','Most scoring models weight payment history most heavily because on-time payment is the strongest signal of reliability. Even one late payment can hurt a score and linger on a report for years. Consistently paying on time is the single best way to build credit.',15,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-finance-credit-a-1','finance','finance:credit','finance-credit-a-1','advanced','mcq','With the debt avalanche repayment method, which debt do you target first?','With the debt avalanche repayment method, which debt do you target first?',ARRAY['The debt with the highest interest rate','The debt with the smallest balance','The newest debt you took on','The debt with the longest term']::text[],ARRAY['The debt with the highest interest rate','The debt with the smallest balance','The newest debt you took on','The debt with the longest term']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'The avalanche method prioritizes the highest-interest debt to minimize total interest paid.','The avalanche method prioritizes the highest-interest debt to minimize total interest paid.','The debt avalanche attacks the highest interest rate first while paying minimums on the rest. Mathematically it minimizes total interest and time to payoff. It contrasts with the snowball method, which targets the smallest balance first for motivational quick wins.','The debt avalanche attacks the highest interest rate first while paying minimums on the rest. Mathematically it minimizes total interest and time to payoff. It contrasts with the snowball method, which targets the smallest balance first for motivational quick wins.',25,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-finance-credit-a-2','finance','finance:credit','finance-credit-a-2','advanced','mcq','Why can closing an old, unused credit card sometimes lower your credit score?','Why can closing an old, unused credit card sometimes lower your credit score?',ARRAY['It can reduce total available credit and shorten average account age','It immediately erases your entire credit history','It always converts the account into a loan','It raises your income on file']::text[],ARRAY['It can reduce total available credit and shorten average account age','It immediately erases your entire credit history','It always converts the account into a loan','It raises your income on file']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Closing a card removes its limit and can raise utilization while reducing average account age.','Closing a card removes its limit and can raise utilization while reducing average account age.','Closing a card eliminates its credit limit, which can push your utilization ratio higher across remaining cards. It may also lower the average age of your accounts over time. Both effects can modestly reduce a score, so keeping old cards open is often wise.','Closing a card eliminates its credit limit, which can push your utilization ratio higher across remaining cards. It may also lower the average age of your accounts over time. Both effects can modestly reduce a score, so keeping old cards open is often wise.',25,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-finance-investing-b-1','finance','finance:investing','finance-investing-b-1','beginner','mcq','What does diversification mean in investing?','What does diversification mean in investing?',ARRAY['Spreading money across many investments to reduce risk','Putting all your money in one promising stock','Avoiding the stock market entirely','Trading as frequently as possible']::text[],ARRAY['Spreading money across many investments to reduce risk','Putting all your money in one promising stock','Avoiding the stock market entirely','Trading as frequently as possible']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Diversification spreads investments across assets so no single loss is devastating.','Diversification spreads investments across assets so no single loss is devastating.','Diversification means holding a mix of investments rather than concentrating in one. Because different assets often move differently, losses in one may be offset by gains in another. This reduces the impact of any single investment performing poorly.','Diversification means holding a mix of investments rather than concentrating in one. Because different assets often move differently, losses in one may be offset by gains in another. This reduces the impact of any single investment performing poorly.',10,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-finance-investing-b-2','finance','finance:investing','finance-investing-b-2','beginner','truefalse','In general, investments offering higher potential returns also tend to carry higher risk.','In general, investments offering higher potential returns also tend to carry higher risk.',ARRAY['True','False']::text[],ARRAY['True','False']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'The risk-return tradeoff means higher expected returns generally come with greater risk.','The risk-return tradeoff means higher expected returns generally come with greater risk.','The risk-return tradeoff is a core investing principle. Assets with higher potential reward, like stocks, typically come with greater volatility and chance of loss. Lower-risk assets, like cash, usually offer smaller returns.','The risk-return tradeoff is a core investing principle. Assets with higher potential reward, like stocks, typically come with greater volatility and chance of loss. Lower-risk assets, like cash, usually offer smaller returns.',10,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-finance-investing-i-1','finance','finance:investing','finance-investing-i-1','intermediate','mcq','What is a key advantage of a low-cost index fund?','What is a key advantage of a low-cost index fund?',ARRAY['It offers broad market exposure with low fees','It guarantees you will beat the market every year','It eliminates all investment risk','It requires picking individual winning stocks']::text[],ARRAY['It offers broad market exposure with low fees','It guarantees you will beat the market every year','It eliminates all investment risk','It requires picking individual winning stocks']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Index funds track a broad market index cheaply, giving wide diversification at low cost.','Index funds track a broad market index cheaply, giving wide diversification at low cost.','An index fund passively tracks a market index rather than trying to beat it. This keeps fees low and provides instant diversification across many holdings. Lower costs and broad exposure are why index funds are a common core holding.','An index fund passively tracks a market index rather than trying to beat it. This keeps fees low and provides instant diversification across many holdings. Lower costs and broad exposure are why index funds are a common core holding.',15,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-finance-investing-i-2','finance','finance:investing','finance-investing-i-2','intermediate','mcq','What does dollar-cost averaging involve?','What does dollar-cost averaging involve?',ARRAY['Investing a fixed amount at regular intervals regardless of price','Investing only when prices reach a yearly low','Selling everything whenever the market drops','Putting your entire savings in at one moment']::text[],ARRAY['Investing a fixed amount at regular intervals regardless of price','Investing only when prices reach a yearly low','Selling everything whenever the market drops','Putting your entire savings in at one moment']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Dollar-cost averaging invests a set amount on a regular schedule, smoothing out price swings.','Dollar-cost averaging invests a set amount on a regular schedule, smoothing out price swings.','Dollar-cost averaging means investing a fixed sum at regular intervals no matter the price. You buy more shares when prices are low and fewer when high, averaging your cost over time. It reduces the pressure to time the market and encourages consistent investing.','Dollar-cost averaging means investing a fixed sum at regular intervals no matter the price. You buy more shares when prices are low and fewer when high, averaging your cost over time. It reduces the pressure to time the market and encourages consistent investing.',15,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-finance-investing-a-1','finance','finance:investing','finance-investing-a-1','advanced','mcq','How does compound interest differ from simple interest over the long term?','How does compound interest differ from simple interest over the long term?',ARRAY['Compound interest earns returns on both the principal and previously earned interest','Compound interest only ever applies to loans, never savings','Compound interest always produces lower totals than simple interest','Compound interest ignores the principal entirely']::text[],ARRAY['Compound interest earns returns on both the principal and previously earned interest','Compound interest only ever applies to loans, never savings','Compound interest always produces lower totals than simple interest','Compound interest ignores the principal entirely']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Compounding earns returns on accumulated interest as well as principal, accelerating growth over time.','Compounding earns returns on accumulated interest as well as principal, accelerating growth over time.','Simple interest is calculated only on the original principal. Compound interest is calculated on the principal plus all previously accumulated interest. Over long periods this compounding effect causes balances to grow far faster, which is why starting early matters so much.','Simple interest is calculated only on the original principal. Compound interest is calculated on the principal plus all previously accumulated interest. Over long periods this compounding effect causes balances to grow far faster, which is why starting early matters so much.',25,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-finance-investing-a-2','finance','finance:investing','finance-investing-a-2','advanced','mcq','What is the main purpose of periodically rebalancing a portfolio?','What is the main purpose of periodically rebalancing a portfolio?',ARRAY['To restore the target mix of assets after market moves shift the weights','To sell all investments and hold only cash','To chase whichever asset rose the most recently','To avoid ever paying any taxes']::text[],ARRAY['To restore the target mix of assets after market moves shift the weights','To sell all investments and hold only cash','To chase whichever asset rose the most recently','To avoid ever paying any taxes']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Rebalancing realigns holdings to your intended allocation after returns drift the weights apart.','Rebalancing realigns holdings to your intended allocation after returns drift the weights apart.','Over time, stronger-performing assets grow to occupy a larger share of a portfolio, shifting its risk level. Rebalancing sells some of what has grown and buys what has lagged to restore target weights. This keeps risk aligned with your plan and enforces a disciplined buy-low, sell-high habit.','Over time, stronger-performing assets grow to occupy a larger share of a portfolio, shifting its risk level. Rebalancing sells some of what has grown and buys what has lagged to restore target weights. This keeps risk aligned with your plan and enforces a disciplined buy-low, sell-high habit.',25,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-finance-retirement-b-1','finance','finance:retirement','finance-retirement-b-1','beginner','mcq','What is a primary purpose of a retirement account?','What is a primary purpose of a retirement account?',ARRAY['To save and invest money for income later in life, often with tax advantages','To provide unlimited free withdrawals at any age','To replace the need for any other savings','To avoid earning any investment returns']::text[],ARRAY['To save and invest money for income later in life, often with tax advantages','To provide unlimited free withdrawals at any age','To replace the need for any other savings','To avoid earning any investment returns']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Retirement accounts help you save and invest for later life, usually with tax benefits.','Retirement accounts help you save and invest for later life, usually with tax benefits.','Retirement accounts are designed to help you accumulate money for your non-working years. Many offer tax advantages to encourage long-term saving. In exchange, they often restrict withdrawals until you reach a certain age.','Retirement accounts are designed to help you accumulate money for your non-working years. Many offer tax advantages to encourage long-term saving. In exchange, they often restrict withdrawals until you reach a certain age.',10,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-finance-retirement-b-2','finance','finance:retirement','finance-retirement-b-2','beginner','truefalse','If an employer matches contributions to your retirement plan, contributing at least enough to get the full match is generally a good idea.','If an employer matches contributions to your retirement plan, contributing at least enough to get the full match is generally a good idea.',ARRAY['True','False']::text[],ARRAY['True','False']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'An employer match is essentially free money, so capturing the full match is widely recommended.','An employer match is essentially free money, so capturing the full match is widely recommended.','Many employers match a portion of what you contribute to a workplace retirement plan. That match is additional compensation you only receive if you contribute. Contributing enough to earn the full match is one of the most reliable ways to boost retirement savings.','Many employers match a portion of what you contribute to a workplace retirement plan. That match is additional compensation you only receive if you contribute. Contributing enough to earn the full match is one of the most reliable ways to boost retirement savings.',10,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-finance-retirement-i-1','finance','finance:retirement','finance-retirement-i-1','intermediate','mcq','What is the main difference between a traditional and a Roth retirement account regarding taxes?','What is the main difference between a traditional and a Roth retirement account regarding taxes?',ARRAY['Traditional contributions are typically pre-tax while Roth withdrawals are typically tax-free','Both are taxed identically in every situation','Roth accounts can never be invested in stocks','Traditional accounts are always tax-free at every stage']::text[],ARRAY['Traditional contributions are typically pre-tax while Roth withdrawals are typically tax-free','Both are taxed identically in every situation','Roth accounts can never be invested in stocks','Traditional accounts are always tax-free at every stage']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Traditional accounts generally defer taxes until withdrawal, while Roth accounts are funded after tax and grow tax-free.','Traditional accounts generally defer taxes until withdrawal, while Roth accounts are funded after tax and grow tax-free.','A traditional account often gives a tax break when you contribute, with taxes due on withdrawals in retirement. A Roth account uses after-tax money now, but qualified withdrawals later are tax-free. The choice often hinges on whether you expect a higher tax rate now or in retirement.','A traditional account often gives a tax break when you contribute, with taxes due on withdrawals in retirement. A Roth account uses after-tax money now, but qualified withdrawals later are tax-free. The choice often hinges on whether you expect a higher tax rate now or in retirement.',15,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-finance-retirement-i-2','finance','finance:retirement','finance-retirement-i-2','intermediate','mcq','What is the difference between a tax deduction and a tax credit?','What is the difference between a tax deduction and a tax credit?',ARRAY['A deduction lowers taxable income while a credit directly reduces the tax owed','They are two names for exactly the same thing','A credit increases your taxable income','A deduction always saves more than a credit of equal size']::text[],ARRAY['A deduction lowers taxable income while a credit directly reduces the tax owed','They are two names for exactly the same thing','A credit increases your taxable income','A deduction always saves more than a credit of equal size']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Deductions reduce the income that is taxed, while credits subtract directly from the tax bill.','Deductions reduce the income that is taxed, while credits subtract directly from the tax bill.','A tax deduction reduces the amount of income subject to tax, so its value depends on your tax rate. A tax credit reduces the actual tax you owe dollar for dollar. Because of this, a credit of a given size usually saves more than a deduction of the same size.','A tax deduction reduces the amount of income subject to tax, so its value depends on your tax rate. A tax credit reduces the actual tax you owe dollar for dollar. Because of this, a credit of a given size usually saves more than a deduction of the same size.',15,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-finance-retirement-a-1','finance','finance:retirement','finance-retirement-a-1','advanced','mcq','Why does starting retirement contributions earlier in life have an outsized effect on the final balance?','Why does starting retirement contributions earlier in life have an outsized effect on the final balance?',ARRAY['Earlier contributions have more time to compound, multiplying their growth','Early contributions are taxed at a lower rate by law','Money invested early is exempt from all market risk','Starting early reduces the total amount you must ever contribute to zero']::text[],ARRAY['Earlier contributions have more time to compound, multiplying their growth','Early contributions are taxed at a lower rate by law','Money invested early is exempt from all market risk','Starting early reduces the total amount you must ever contribute to zero']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'More years of compounding mean early contributions grow far larger than identical later ones.','More years of compounding mean early contributions grow far larger than identical later ones.','Time is the most powerful lever in retirement saving because of compounding. A dollar invested in your twenties has decades to earn returns on returns, while the same dollar invested later has less time to grow. This is why even small early contributions can outweigh larger ones made later.','Time is the most powerful lever in retirement saving because of compounding. A dollar invested in your twenties has decades to earn returns on returns, while the same dollar invested later has less time to grow. This is why even small early contributions can outweigh larger ones made later.',25,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-finance-retirement-a-2','finance','finance:retirement','finance-retirement-a-2','advanced','mcq','What does the concept of asset location (as opposed to allocation) refer to?','What does the concept of asset location (as opposed to allocation) refer to?',ARRAY['Choosing which type of account holds each investment to improve tax efficiency','Deciding the overall percentage split between stocks and bonds','Picking which country to retire in','Storing physical share certificates in a safe place']::text[],ARRAY['Choosing which type of account holds each investment to improve tax efficiency','Deciding the overall percentage split between stocks and bonds','Picking which country to retire in','Storing physical share certificates in a safe place']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Asset location places investments in taxable or tax-advantaged accounts to minimize taxes.','Asset location places investments in taxable or tax-advantaged accounts to minimize taxes.','Asset allocation decides your overall mix of investments, while asset location decides which account type holds each one. Placing tax-inefficient assets in tax-advantaged accounts and tax-efficient ones in taxable accounts can reduce the taxes you pay. Thoughtful location can improve after-tax returns without changing your overall allocation.','Asset allocation decides your overall mix of investments, while asset location decides which account type holds each one. Placing tax-inefficient assets in tax-advantaged accounts and tax-efficient ones in taxable accounts can reduce the taxes you pay. Thoughtful location can improve after-tax returns without changing your overall allocation.',25,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bank-data-averages-1','data','data:averages','data-averages-1','beginner','mcq','A student scores 4, 8, and 9 on three quizzes. What is the mean (average) of these scores?','A student scores 4, 8, and 9 on three quizzes. What is the mean (average) of these scores?',ARRAY['7','8','9','21']::text[],ARRAY['7','8','9','21']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'The mean is the sum divided by the count: (4 + 8 + 9) / 3 = 21 / 3 = 7.','The mean is the sum divided by the count: (4 + 8 + 9) / 3 = 21 / 3 = 7.','The mean is found by adding all values together and dividing by how many values there are. It gives a single number that represents the typical size of the values. Because every value contributes to the total, the mean can be pulled up or down by unusually large or small numbers.','The mean is found by adding all values together and dividing by how many values there are. It gives a single number that represents the typical size of the values. Because every value contributes to the total, the mean can be pulled up or down by unusually large or small numbers.',10,'approved','curated-taste');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bank-data-averages-2','data','data:averages','data-averages-2','intermediate','mcq','Five houses on a street sold for $200k, $210k, $220k, $230k, and $5,000k (a mansion). Which measure best describes a ''typical'' house price on this street?','Five houses on a street sold for $200k, $210k, $220k, $230k, and $5,000k (a mansion). Which measure best describes a ''typical'' house price on this street?',ARRAY['The median, because it is not distorted by the one extreme value','The mean, because it uses every value','The range, because it shows the full spread','The mode, because prices repeat']::text[],ARRAY['The median, because it is not distorted by the one extreme value','The mean, because it uses every value','The range, because it shows the full spread','The mode, because prices repeat']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'The single $5,000k mansion is an outlier that inflates the mean to over $1,000k, while the median of $220k stays close to the cluster of ordinary homes.','The single $5,000k mansion is an outlier that inflates the mean to over $1,000k, while the median of $220k stays close to the cluster of ordinary homes.','The median is the middle value when data is sorted in order, so it ignores how far away extreme values are. The mean, by contrast, is sensitive to outliers because every value is added into the total. When data is skewed by a few extreme points, the median usually describes the ''typical'' case more honestly.','The median is the middle value when data is sorted in order, so it ignores how far away extreme values are. The mean, by contrast, is sensitive to outliers because every value is added into the total. When data is skewed by a few extreme points, the median usually describes the ''typical'' case more honestly.',15,'approved','curated-taste');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bank-data-averages-3','data','data:averages','data-averages-3','advanced','mcq','Two classes both have a mean test score of 70. Class A''s scores are all between 68 and 72, while Class B''s scores range from 40 to 100. Which statement is correct?','Two classes both have a mean test score of 70. Class A''s scores are all between 68 and 72, while Class B''s scores range from 40 to 100. Which statement is correct?',ARRAY['Class B has a larger standard deviation because its scores are more spread out','Class A has a larger standard deviation because it has more students near the mean','Both classes must have the same standard deviation because the means are equal','Standard deviation cannot be compared unless the medians are equal']::text[],ARRAY['Class B has a larger standard deviation because its scores are more spread out','Class A has a larger standard deviation because it has more students near the mean','Both classes must have the same standard deviation because the means are equal','Standard deviation cannot be compared unless the medians are equal']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Standard deviation measures spread around the mean, and Class B''s scores deviate much further from 70 than Class A''s tightly clustered scores, so Class B''s standard deviation is larger.','Standard deviation measures spread around the mean, and Class B''s scores deviate much further from 70 than Class A''s tightly clustered scores, so Class B''s standard deviation is larger.','Standard deviation summarizes how far, on average, values sit from the mean. A small standard deviation means values cluster tightly around the mean; a large one means they are widely scattered. Two data sets can share the same mean yet have very different standard deviations, which is why spread matters as much as the average.','Standard deviation summarizes how far, on average, values sit from the mean. A small standard deviation means values cluster tightly around the mean; a large one means they are widely scattered. Two data sets can share the same mean yet have very different standard deviations, which is why spread matters as much as the average.',25,'approved','curated-taste');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bank-data-probability-1','data','data:probability','data-probability-1','beginner','mcq','You roll a single fair six-sided die. What is the probability of rolling a 4?','You roll a single fair six-sided die. What is the probability of rolling a 4?',ARRAY['1/6','1/4','4/6','1/2']::text[],ARRAY['1/6','1/4','4/6','1/2']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'There is exactly one face showing a 4 out of six equally likely faces, so the probability is 1/6.','There is exactly one face showing a 4 out of six equally likely faces, so the probability is 1/6.','For equally likely outcomes, probability equals the number of favorable outcomes divided by the total number of outcomes. A fair die has six faces that are all equally likely, so each single value has a probability of one in six. Probabilities always fall between 0 (impossible) and 1 (certain).','For equally likely outcomes, probability equals the number of favorable outcomes divided by the total number of outcomes. A fair die has six faces that are all equally likely, so each single value has a probability of one in six. Probabilities always fall between 0 (impossible) and 1 (certain).',10,'approved','curated-taste');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bank-data-probability-2','data','data:probability','data-probability-2','intermediate','mcq','You flip a fair coin twice. What is the probability of getting heads on both flips?','You flip a fair coin twice. What is the probability of getting heads on both flips?',ARRAY['1/4','1/2','2/4 plus 1','3/4']::text[],ARRAY['1/4','1/2','2/4 plus 1','3/4']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'The flips are independent, so you multiply the probabilities: (1/2) x (1/2) = 1/4.','The flips are independent, so you multiply the probabilities: (1/2) x (1/2) = 1/4.','When two events are independent, meaning one does not affect the other, the probability that both happen is the product of their individual probabilities. Each coin flip has a 1/2 chance of heads, so two heads in a row is 1/2 times 1/2. Listing all outcomes (HH, HT, TH, TT) confirms that only one of four equally likely results is two heads.','When two events are independent, meaning one does not affect the other, the probability that both happen is the product of their individual probabilities. Each coin flip has a 1/2 chance of heads, so two heads in a row is 1/2 times 1/2. Listing all outcomes (HH, HT, TH, TT) confirms that only one of four equally likely results is two heads.',15,'approved','curated-taste');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bank-data-probability-3','data','data:probability','data-probability-3','advanced','mcq','A bag has 3 red and 2 blue marbles. You draw two marbles without replacement. What is the probability that both are red?','A bag has 3 red and 2 blue marbles. You draw two marbles without replacement. What is the probability that both are red?',ARRAY['3/10','9/25','3/5','1/2']::text[],ARRAY['3/10','9/25','3/5','1/2']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'The first red has probability 3/5; after removing it, the second red has probability 2/4, so (3/5) x (2/4) = 6/20 = 3/10.','The first red has probability 3/5; after removing it, the second red has probability 2/4, so (3/5) x (2/4) = 6/20 = 3/10.','Drawing without replacement makes events dependent, because removing a marble changes what remains for the next draw. You multiply the probability of the first event by the conditional probability of the second given the first. This differs from drawing with replacement, where the counts reset and the draws stay independent.','Drawing without replacement makes events dependent, because removing a marble changes what remains for the next draw. You multiply the probability of the first event by the conditional probability of the second given the first. This differs from drawing with replacement, where the counts reset and the draws stay independent.',25,'approved','curated-taste');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bank-data-charts-1','data','data:charts','data-charts-1','beginner','mcq','A bar chart shows weekly sales: Monday 10, Tuesday 25, Wednesday 15, and Thursday 30. Which day had the highest sales?','A bar chart shows weekly sales: Monday 10, Tuesday 25, Wednesday 15, and Thursday 30. Which day had the highest sales?',ARRAY['Thursday','Tuesday','Monday','Wednesday']::text[],ARRAY['Thursday','Tuesday','Monday','Wednesday']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Thursday''s value of 30 is larger than 10, 25, and 15, so it has the tallest bar and the highest sales.','Thursday''s value of 30 is larger than 10, 25, and 15, so it has the tallest bar and the highest sales.','In a bar chart, the height (or length) of each bar represents its value, so taller bars mean larger quantities. To compare categories you simply compare bar heights. Bar charts are best for comparing distinct, separate categories rather than showing continuous change over time.','In a bar chart, the height (or length) of each bar represents its value, so taller bars mean larger quantities. To compare categories you simply compare bar heights. Bar charts are best for comparing distinct, separate categories rather than showing continuous change over time.',10,'approved','curated-taste');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bank-data-charts-2','data','data:charts','data-charts-2','intermediate','mcq','A pie chart of a budget shows Rent at 50%, Food at 25%, and Transport at 25%. If the total monthly budget is $2,000, how much is spent on Food?','A pie chart of a budget shows Rent at 50%, Food at 25%, and Transport at 25%. If the total monthly budget is $2,000, how much is spent on Food?',ARRAY['$500','$1,000','$250','$750']::text[],ARRAY['$500','$1,000','$250','$750']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Food is 25% of the budget, and 25% of $2,000 is 0.25 x 2,000 = $500.','Food is 25% of the budget, and 25% of $2,000 is 0.25 x 2,000 = $500.','A pie chart divides a whole into slices, where each slice''s share of the circle equals its percentage of the total. To find an actual amount, convert the percentage to a decimal and multiply by the whole. Pie charts work well when parts add up to a meaningful 100% but become hard to read with many small slices.','A pie chart divides a whole into slices, where each slice''s share of the circle equals its percentage of the total. To find an actual amount, convert the percentage to a decimal and multiply by the whole. Pie charts work well when parts add up to a meaningful 100% but become hard to read with many small slices.',15,'approved','curated-taste');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bank-data-charts-3','data','data:charts','data-charts-3','advanced','mcq','A bar chart compares two products. Their actual sales are 100 and 110 units, but the vertical axis starts at 95 instead of 0, making the second bar look about three times taller. Why is this chart misleading?','A bar chart compares two products. Their actual sales are 100 and 110 units, but the vertical axis starts at 95 instead of 0, making the second bar look about three times taller. Why is this chart misleading?',ARRAY['A truncated axis that does not start at zero exaggerates small differences','Bar charts can never be used to compare two products','The bars should be replaced with a pie chart','The difference of 10 units is too large to show accurately']::text[],ARRAY['A truncated axis that does not start at zero exaggerates small differences','Bar charts can never be used to compare two products','The bars should be replaced with a pie chart','The difference of 10 units is too large to show accurately']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Starting the axis at 95 rather than 0 cuts off most of each bar, so a real difference of only 10 units appears visually enormous.','Starting the axis at 95 rather than 0 cuts off most of each bar, so a real difference of only 10 units appears visually enormous.','When a bar chart''s value axis does not begin at zero, the visible bar heights no longer represent the true proportions between values. A small real difference can be stretched to look dramatic, which is a common way charts mislead. A careful reader always checks where the axis starts before trusting how big a difference looks.','When a bar chart''s value axis does not begin at zero, the visible bar heights no longer represent the true proportions between values. A small real difference can be stretched to look dramatic, which is a common way charts mislead. A careful reader always checks where the axis starts before trusting how big a difference looks.',25,'approved','curated-taste');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bank-data-studies-1','data','data:studies','data-studies-1','beginner','truefalse','True or False: If two things are correlated (they tend to rise and fall together), that proves one of them causes the other.','True or False: If two things are correlated (they tend to rise and fall together), that proves one of them causes the other.',ARRAY['True','False']::text[],ARRAY['True','False']::text[],1,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Correlation alone does not prove causation, because a third factor or pure coincidence could explain why two things move together.','Correlation alone does not prove causation, because a third factor or pure coincidence could explain why two things move together.','Correlation means two variables tend to change together, but it does not reveal why. The link could run in either direction, be caused by a hidden third variable, or be coincidence. Establishing causation usually requires a controlled experiment, not just an observed pattern.','Correlation means two variables tend to change together, but it does not reveal why. The link could run in either direction, be caused by a hidden third variable, or be coincidence. Establishing causation usually requires a controlled experiment, not just an observed pattern.',10,'approved','curated-taste');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bank-data-studies-2','data','data:studies','data-studies-2','intermediate','mcq','A researcher surveys people leaving a luxury gym about their income and concludes the whole city is wealthy. What is the main flaw in this study?','A researcher surveys people leaving a luxury gym about their income and concludes the whole city is wealthy. What is the main flaw in this study?',ARRAY['The sample is not representative of the whole city','The sample size of a gym is always too small','Income cannot be measured by a survey','Surveys are never valid research tools']::text[],ARRAY['The sample is not representative of the whole city','The sample size of a gym is always too small','Income cannot be measured by a survey','Surveys are never valid research tools']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'People at a luxury gym are not a random cross-section of the city, so the sample is biased toward wealthier residents and cannot represent everyone.','People at a luxury gym are not a random cross-section of the city, so the sample is biased toward wealthier residents and cannot represent everyone.','A study''s conclusions are only as trustworthy as its sample. When the sample is drawn from a group that differs systematically from the whole population, this is called sampling bias. To generalize to a population, you need a sample that is representative, ideally chosen at random.','A study''s conclusions are only as trustworthy as its sample. When the sample is drawn from a group that differs systematically from the whole population, this is called sampling bias. To generalize to a population, you need a sample that is representative, ideally chosen at random.',15,'approved','curated-taste');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bank-data-studies-3','data','data:studies','data-studies-3','advanced','mcq','A study finds towns with more ice cream sales also have more drownings, and concludes ice cream causes drowning. What is the most likely real explanation?','A study finds towns with more ice cream sales also have more drownings, and concludes ice cream causes drowning. What is the most likely real explanation?',ARRAY['Hot summer weather is a confounding variable that increases both ice cream sales and swimming','Ice cream genuinely makes people more likely to drown','Drowning makes people crave ice cream','The two variables are completely unrelated by chance alone']::text[],ARRAY['Hot summer weather is a confounding variable that increases both ice cream sales and swimming','Ice cream genuinely makes people more likely to drown','Drowning makes people crave ice cream','The two variables are completely unrelated by chance alone']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Warm weather independently drives both more ice cream purchases and more swimming (and thus drownings), creating a correlation without any direct causal link between the two.','Warm weather independently drives both more ice cream purchases and more swimming (and thus drownings), creating a correlation without any direct causal link between the two.','A confounding variable is a hidden third factor that influences both of the variables you are comparing, creating a misleading correlation between them. Failing to account for confounders is a classic source of false causal claims. Good studies try to control for or randomize away such hidden factors so the true relationship can be seen.','A confounding variable is a hidden third factor that influences both of the variables you are comparing, creating a misleading correlation between them. Failing to account for confounders is a classic source of false causal claims. Good studies try to control for or randomize away such hidden factors so the true relationship can be seen.',25,'approved','curated-taste');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-data-averages-b-1','data','data:averages','data-averages-b-1','beginner','mcq','What is the mean (average) of the numbers 4, 8, and 9?','What is the mean (average) of the numbers 4, 8, and 9?',ARRAY['7','8','21','6']::text[],ARRAY['7','8','21','6']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Add the values to get 21, then divide by 3 to get 7.','Add the values to get 21, then divide by 3 to get 7.','The mean is found by adding all the values together and dividing by how many values there are. It is the most common type of average. It can be pulled toward unusually large or small values.','The mean is found by adding all the values together and dividing by how many values there are. It is the most common type of average. It can be pulled toward unusually large or small values.',10,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-data-averages-b-2','data','data:averages','data-averages-b-2','beginner','mcq','What is the median of the sorted list 2, 5, 7, 10, 14?','What is the median of the sorted list 2, 5, 7, 10, 14?',ARRAY['7','5','10','8']::text[],ARRAY['7','5','10','8']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'With five values, the median is the middle (third) value, which is 7.','With five values, the median is the middle (third) value, which is 7.','The median is the middle value when the data is sorted in order. For an odd count it is the single central value; for an even count it is the average of the two central values. It is less affected by extreme values than the mean.','The median is the middle value when the data is sorted in order. For an odd count it is the single central value; for an even count it is the average of the two central values. It is less affected by extreme values than the mean.',10,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-data-averages-i-1','data','data:averages','data-averages-i-1','intermediate','mcq','A dataset is 3, 3, 4, 5, 100. Which measure best describes a typical value, given the outlier?','A dataset is 3, 3, 4, 5, 100. Which measure best describes a typical value, given the outlier?',ARRAY['The median (4)','The mean (23)','The range (97)','The maximum (100)']::text[],ARRAY['The median (4)','The mean (23)','The range (97)','The maximum (100)']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'The mean of 23 is distorted by the outlier 100, while the median of 4 reflects a typical value.','The mean of 23 is distorted by the outlier 100, while the median of 4 reflects a typical value.','Outliers are values far from the rest of the data. The mean is sensitive to outliers because every value affects the sum, but the median is resistant because it depends only on position. When data is skewed or has outliers, the median often describes a typical value better.','Outliers are values far from the rest of the data. The mean is sensitive to outliers because every value affects the sum, but the median is resistant because it depends only on position. When data is skewed or has outliers, the median often describes a typical value better.',15,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-data-averages-i-2','data','data:averages','data-averages-i-2','intermediate','mcq','What is the mode of the dataset 6, 2, 6, 9, 2, 6?','What is the mode of the dataset 6, 2, 6, 9, 2, 6?',ARRAY['6','2','9','There is no mode']::text[],ARRAY['6','2','9','There is no mode']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'The value 6 appears three times, more often than any other value.','The value 6 appears three times, more often than any other value.','The mode is the value that occurs most frequently in a dataset. A dataset can have one mode, more than one mode, or no mode if all values appear equally often. The mode is the only average that can be used with non-numeric categories.','The mode is the value that occurs most frequently in a dataset. A dataset can have one mode, more than one mode, or no mode if all values appear equally often. The mode is the only average that can be used with non-numeric categories.',15,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-data-averages-a-1','data','data:averages','data-averages-a-1','advanced','mcq','Two classes both have a mean test score of 70. Class A scores cluster between 65 and 75; Class B has many scores near 40 and near 100. Which statement is correct?','Two classes both have a mean test score of 70. Class A scores cluster between 65 and 75; Class B has many scores near 40 and near 100. Which statement is correct?',ARRAY['Class B has a larger standard deviation than Class A','Class A has a larger standard deviation than Class B','Both classes have the same standard deviation','Standard deviation cannot differ when means are equal']::text[],ARRAY['Class B has a larger standard deviation than Class A','Class A has a larger standard deviation than Class B','Both classes have the same standard deviation','Standard deviation cannot differ when means are equal']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Class B''s scores are spread far from the mean, giving it a larger standard deviation despite the equal means.','Class B''s scores are spread far from the mean, giving it a larger standard deviation despite the equal means.','Standard deviation measures how spread out values are around the mean. A small standard deviation means values cluster tightly near the mean; a large one means they are widely scattered. Two datasets can share a mean yet have very different spreads.','Standard deviation measures how spread out values are around the mean. A small standard deviation means values cluster tightly near the mean; a large one means they are widely scattered. Two datasets can share a mean yet have very different spreads.',25,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-data-averages-a-2','data','data:averages','data-averages-a-2','advanced','truefalse','True or false: Adding a value equal to the current mean to a dataset leaves the mean unchanged.','True or false: Adding a value equal to the current mean to a dataset leaves the mean unchanged.',ARRAY['True','False']::text[],ARRAY['True','False']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Adding a value equal to the mean increases the sum and count proportionally, so the mean stays the same.','Adding a value equal to the mean increases the sum and count proportionally, so the mean stays the same.','The mean balances the data so that deviations above and below it cancel out. Adding a new value equal to the mean contributes zero net deviation, leaving the balance point fixed. Adding a value above or below the mean would shift the mean in that direction.','The mean balances the data so that deviations above and below it cancel out. Adding a new value equal to the mean contributes zero net deviation, leaving the balance point fixed. Adding a value above or below the mean would shift the mean in that direction.',25,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-data-probability-b-1','data','data:probability','data-probability-b-1','beginner','mcq','What is the probability of rolling a 3 on a fair six-sided die?','What is the probability of rolling a 3 on a fair six-sided die?',ARRAY['1/6','1/3','3/6','1/2']::text[],ARRAY['1/6','1/3','3/6','1/2']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'There is one favorable outcome (a 3) out of six equally likely outcomes, giving 1/6.','There is one favorable outcome (a 3) out of six equally likely outcomes, giving 1/6.','Probability is the number of favorable outcomes divided by the total number of equally likely outcomes. It ranges from 0 (impossible) to 1 (certain). For a fair die, each of the six faces is equally likely.','Probability is the number of favorable outcomes divided by the total number of equally likely outcomes. It ranges from 0 (impossible) to 1 (certain). For a fair die, each of the six faces is equally likely.',10,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-data-probability-b-2','data','data:probability','data-probability-b-2','beginner','mcq','A bag has 3 red and 7 blue marbles. What is the probability of drawing a red marble at random?','A bag has 3 red and 7 blue marbles. What is the probability of drawing a red marble at random?',ARRAY['3/10','7/10','3/7','1/3']::text[],ARRAY['3/10','7/10','3/7','1/3']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'There are 3 red marbles out of 10 total, so the probability is 3/10.','There are 3 red marbles out of 10 total, so the probability is 3/10.','When outcomes are equally likely, probability equals favorable outcomes over total outcomes. Here every marble is equally likely to be drawn. The total is the sum of all marbles, not just one color.','When outcomes are equally likely, probability equals favorable outcomes over total outcomes. Here every marble is equally likely to be drawn. The total is the sum of all marbles, not just one color.',10,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-data-probability-i-1','data','data:probability','data-probability-i-1','intermediate','mcq','If the probability that it rains tomorrow is 0.3, what is the probability that it does not rain?','If the probability that it rains tomorrow is 0.3, what is the probability that it does not rain?',ARRAY['0.7','0.3','0.5','1.3']::text[],ARRAY['0.7','0.3','0.5','1.3']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'The complement of an event is 1 minus its probability, so 1 - 0.3 = 0.7.','The complement of an event is 1 minus its probability, so 1 - 0.3 = 0.7.','The complement of an event is everything that is not that event. Because something must happen, the probability of an event and its complement add up to 1. So the probability of ''not rain'' is 1 minus the probability of rain.','The complement of an event is everything that is not that event. Because something must happen, the probability of an event and its complement add up to 1. So the probability of ''not rain'' is 1 minus the probability of rain.',15,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-data-probability-i-2','data','data:probability','data-probability-i-2','intermediate','mcq','You flip a fair coin twice. What is the probability of getting heads both times?','You flip a fair coin twice. What is the probability of getting heads both times?',ARRAY['1/4','1/2','1/3','2/4']::text[],ARRAY['1/4','1/2','1/3','2/4']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Each flip is independent with probability 1/2, so 1/2 x 1/2 = 1/4.','Each flip is independent with probability 1/2, so 1/2 x 1/2 = 1/4.','Two events are independent when one does not affect the other. For independent events, the probability that both happen is the product of their individual probabilities. Two coin flips are independent, so you multiply 1/2 by 1/2.','Two events are independent when one does not affect the other. For independent events, the probability that both happen is the product of their individual probabilities. Two coin flips are independent, so you multiply 1/2 by 1/2.',15,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-data-probability-a-1','data','data:probability','data-probability-a-1','advanced','mcq','A test for a rare disease is 99% accurate, but the disease affects only 1 in 1000 people. If someone tests positive, the chance they actually have the disease is closest to:','A test for a rare disease is 99% accurate, but the disease affects only 1 in 1000 people. If someone tests positive, the chance they actually have the disease is closest to:',ARRAY['About 9%','About 99%','About 50%','About 1%']::text[],ARRAY['About 9%','About 99%','About 50%','About 1%']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Because the disease is rare, false positives from the healthy majority outnumber true positives, so the true-positive rate is only around 9%.','Because the disease is rare, false positives from the healthy majority outnumber true positives, so the true-positive rate is only around 9%.','When a condition is rare, even an accurate test produces many false positives relative to true positives, a result known as the base rate fallacy. The chance of truly having the condition given a positive test depends heavily on how common the condition is. This is why screening rare events can be misleading without considering the base rate.','When a condition is rare, even an accurate test produces many false positives relative to true positives, a result known as the base rate fallacy. The chance of truly having the condition given a positive test depends heavily on how common the condition is. This is why screening rare events can be misleading without considering the base rate.',25,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-data-probability-a-2','data','data:probability','data-probability-a-2','advanced','truefalse','True or false: After a fair coin lands heads five times in a row, the next flip is more likely to be tails.','True or false: After a fair coin lands heads five times in a row, the next flip is more likely to be tails.',ARRAY['True','False']::text[],ARRAY['True','False']::text[],1,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Each flip is independent, so the probability of tails remains 1/2 regardless of past results.','Each flip is independent, so the probability of tails remains 1/2 regardless of past results.','The gambler''s fallacy is the mistaken belief that past independent outcomes change future probabilities. A fair coin has no memory, so each flip stays at 1/2 no matter what came before. Past streaks do not make a balancing outcome more likely.','The gambler''s fallacy is the mistaken belief that past independent outcomes change future probabilities. A fair coin has no memory, so each flip stays at 1/2 no matter what came before. Past streaks do not make a balancing outcome more likely.',25,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-data-charts-b-1','data','data:charts','data-charts-b-1','beginner','mcq','A bar chart shows sales: Monday 10, Tuesday 25, Wednesday 15, Thursday 30. Which day had the highest sales?','A bar chart shows sales: Monday 10, Tuesday 25, Wednesday 15, Thursday 30. Which day had the highest sales?',ARRAY['Thursday','Tuesday','Wednesday','Monday']::text[],ARRAY['Thursday','Tuesday','Wednesday','Monday']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Thursday''s value of 30 is the largest, so its bar is the tallest.','Thursday''s value of 30 is the largest, so its bar is the tallest.','A bar chart represents values with the heights or lengths of bars, making comparisons across categories easy. The tallest bar corresponds to the largest value. Bar charts are best for comparing separate categories rather than showing trends over continuous time.','A bar chart represents values with the heights or lengths of bars, making comparisons across categories easy. The tallest bar corresponds to the largest value. Bar charts are best for comparing separate categories rather than showing trends over continuous time.',10,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-data-charts-b-2','data','data:charts','data-charts-b-2','beginner','mcq','A pie chart of a budget shows Rent 50%, Food 25%, Transport 15%, and Savings as the remainder. What percentage is Savings?','A pie chart of a budget shows Rent 50%, Food 25%, Transport 15%, and Savings as the remainder. What percentage is Savings?',ARRAY['10%','15%','25%','5%']::text[],ARRAY['10%','15%','25%','5%']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'The slices must sum to 100%, so Savings is 100 - 50 - 25 - 15 = 10%.','The slices must sum to 100%, so Savings is 100 - 50 - 25 - 15 = 10%.','A pie chart shows how a whole is divided into parts, with each slice proportional to its share. All slices together must add up to 100%. To find a missing slice, subtract the known slices from 100%.','A pie chart shows how a whole is divided into parts, with each slice proportional to its share. All slices together must add up to 100%. To find a missing slice, subtract the known slices from 100%.',10,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-data-charts-i-1','data','data:charts','data-charts-i-1','intermediate','mcq','A line graph shows monthly revenue rising from 100 in January to 160 in March. What is the overall trend?','A line graph shows monthly revenue rising from 100 in January to 160 in March. What is the overall trend?',ARRAY['Increasing','Decreasing','Flat','Cyclical with no net change']::text[],ARRAY['Increasing','Decreasing','Flat','Cyclical with no net change']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Revenue moves upward from 100 to 160 over the period, indicating an increasing trend.','Revenue moves upward from 100 to 160 over the period, indicating an increasing trend.','A line graph connects data points over a continuous variable such as time, making trends easy to see. An upward slope shows growth and a downward slope shows decline. Reading the start and end points reveals the overall direction of change.','A line graph connects data points over a continuous variable such as time, making trends easy to see. An upward slope shows growth and a downward slope shows decline. Reading the start and end points reveals the overall direction of change.',15,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-data-charts-i-2','data','data:charts','data-charts-i-2','intermediate','mcq','A bar chart''s vertical axis starts at 90 instead of 0, making a bar of 100 look twice as tall as a bar of 95. What problem does this create?','A bar chart''s vertical axis starts at 90 instead of 0, making a bar of 100 look twice as tall as a bar of 95. What problem does this create?',ARRAY['It exaggerates small differences between values','It makes the values easier to read accurately','It changes the actual data values','It has no effect on interpretation']::text[],ARRAY['It exaggerates small differences between values','It makes the values easier to read accurately','It changes the actual data values','It has no effect on interpretation']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'A truncated axis that does not start at zero visually magnifies small differences, misleading the viewer.','A truncated axis that does not start at zero visually magnifies small differences, misleading the viewer.','When a bar chart''s value axis does not start at zero, the relative heights of bars no longer reflect the true ratios between values. Small differences can appear dramatic, which can mislead viewers. Always check the axis range before judging how big a difference really is.','When a bar chart''s value axis does not start at zero, the relative heights of bars no longer reflect the true ratios between values. Small differences can appear dramatic, which can mislead viewers. Always check the axis range before judging how big a difference really is.',15,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-data-charts-a-1','data','data:charts','data-charts-a-1','advanced','mcq','A scatter plot shows that as study hours increase, exam scores tend to increase, with points sloping upward. This pattern indicates:','A scatter plot shows that as study hours increase, exam scores tend to increase, with points sloping upward. This pattern indicates:',ARRAY['A positive correlation','A negative correlation','No correlation','That studying causes higher scores for certain']::text[],ARRAY['A positive correlation','A negative correlation','No correlation','That studying causes higher scores for certain']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Points sloping upward together indicate a positive correlation between the two variables.','Points sloping upward together indicate a positive correlation between the two variables.','A scatter plot displays the relationship between two numeric variables, one on each axis. An upward pattern is a positive correlation and a downward pattern is a negative correlation. Correlation describes association only and does not by itself prove that one variable causes the other.','A scatter plot displays the relationship between two numeric variables, one on each axis. An upward pattern is a positive correlation and a downward pattern is a negative correlation. Correlation describes association only and does not by itself prove that one variable causes the other.',25,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-data-charts-a-2','data','data:charts','data-charts-a-2','advanced','mcq','A histogram of incomes has a long tail stretching to the right toward very high values. This distribution is described as:','A histogram of incomes has a long tail stretching to the right toward very high values. This distribution is described as:',ARRAY['Right-skewed','Left-skewed','Symmetric','Uniform']::text[],ARRAY['Right-skewed','Left-skewed','Symmetric','Uniform']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'A tail extending toward the high (right) end of the axis indicates a right-skewed distribution.','A tail extending toward the high (right) end of the axis indicates a right-skewed distribution.','A histogram groups numeric data into bins and shows their frequencies as bars. Skew refers to the direction of a long tail: a right-skewed distribution has a tail toward higher values. In right-skewed data the mean is typically pulled above the median by the high values.','A histogram groups numeric data into bins and shows their frequencies as bars. Skew refers to the direction of a long tail: a right-skewed distribution has a tail toward higher values. In right-skewed data the mean is typically pulled above the median by the high values.',25,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-data-studies-b-1','data','data:studies','data-studies-b-1','beginner','truefalse','True or false: A survey of only a company''s own employees is a reliable way to measure the general public''s opinion of that company.','True or false: A survey of only a company''s own employees is a reliable way to measure the general public''s opinion of that company.',ARRAY['True','False']::text[],ARRAY['True','False']::text[],1,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Employees are not representative of the general public, so the sample is biased.','Employees are not representative of the general public, so the sample is biased.','A sample should represent the larger population you want to study. When a sample is drawn from an unrepresentative group, the results suffer from selection bias. Conclusions about the public require a sample that actually reflects the public.','A sample should represent the larger population you want to study. When a sample is drawn from an unrepresentative group, the results suffer from selection bias. Conclusions about the public require a sample that actually reflects the public.',10,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-data-studies-b-2','data','data:studies','data-studies-b-2','beginner','mcq','Ice cream sales and drowning deaths both rise in summer. What is the most likely explanation?','Ice cream sales and drowning deaths both rise in summer. What is the most likely explanation?',ARRAY['A third factor, hot weather, drives both','Ice cream causes drowning','Drowning causes ice cream sales','The link is impossible to explain']::text[],ARRAY['A third factor, hot weather, drives both','Ice cream causes drowning','Drowning causes ice cream sales','The link is impossible to explain']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Warm weather independently increases both swimming and ice cream consumption, creating a spurious link.','Warm weather independently increases both swimming and ice cream consumption, creating a spurious link.','Two things can rise and fall together without one causing the other. Often a third variable, called a confounder, influences both. Correlation alone does not establish causation.','Two things can rise and fall together without one causing the other. Often a third variable, called a confounder, influences both. Correlation alone does not establish causation.',10,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-data-studies-i-1','data','data:studies','data-studies-i-1','intermediate','mcq','A study finds people who drink coffee live longer, but coffee drinkers also exercise more. Exercise here is best described as:','A study finds people who drink coffee live longer, but coffee drinkers also exercise more. Exercise here is best described as:',ARRAY['A confounding variable','The outcome variable','A random error','A placebo effect']::text[],ARRAY['A confounding variable','The outcome variable','A random error','A placebo effect']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Exercise is associated with both coffee drinking and longevity, so it confounds the observed link.','Exercise is associated with both coffee drinking and longevity, so it confounds the observed link.','A confounding variable is associated with both the supposed cause and the outcome, distorting the apparent relationship. If confounders are not controlled, an observed association may be misleading. Well-designed studies try to account for confounders before claiming a cause.','A confounding variable is associated with both the supposed cause and the outcome, distorting the apparent relationship. If confounders are not controlled, an observed association may be misleading. Well-designed studies try to account for confounders before claiming a cause.',15,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-data-studies-i-2','data','data:studies','data-studies-i-2','intermediate','mcq','Why is a randomized controlled trial considered stronger evidence of causation than an observational study?','Why is a randomized controlled trial considered stronger evidence of causation than an observational study?',ARRAY['Random assignment balances out confounding factors between groups','It always uses a larger sample size','It avoids using any statistics','It guarantees the result is true']::text[],ARRAY['Random assignment balances out confounding factors between groups','It always uses a larger sample size','It avoids using any statistics','It guarantees the result is true']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Randomly assigning participants tends to balance known and unknown confounders across groups, isolating the treatment''s effect.','Randomly assigning participants tends to balance known and unknown confounders across groups, isolating the treatment''s effect.','In a randomized controlled trial, participants are assigned to treatment or control groups by chance. Randomization tends to distribute confounding factors evenly, so differences in outcomes can be attributed to the treatment. Observational studies lack this control, making causal claims weaker.','In a randomized controlled trial, participants are assigned to treatment or control groups by chance. Randomization tends to distribute confounding factors evenly, so differences in outcomes can be attributed to the treatment. Observational studies lack this control, making causal claims weaker.',15,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-data-studies-a-1','data','data:studies','data-studies-a-1','advanced','mcq','A weight-loss ad reports an ''average loss of 20 pounds,'' but most participants lost about 5 pounds while a few lost over 60. Which is the likely issue?','A weight-loss ad reports an ''average loss of 20 pounds,'' but most participants lost about 5 pounds while a few lost over 60. Which is the likely issue?',ARRAY['The mean is inflated by a few extreme results, so the median would be more honest','The median is too high to report','The data must be fabricated','Twenty pounds is the most common result']::text[],ARRAY['The mean is inflated by a few extreme results, so the median would be more honest','The median is too high to report','The data must be fabricated','Twenty pounds is the most common result']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'A few very large losses pull the mean upward, making it unrepresentative of a typical participant.','A few very large losses pull the mean upward, making it unrepresentative of a typical participant.','When results are skewed, the mean can be dominated by a few extreme values and overstate the typical outcome. Advertisers may choose the mean precisely because it sounds more impressive. The median better reflects what a typical participant experienced.','When results are skewed, the mean can be dominated by a few extreme values and overstate the typical outcome. Advertisers may choose the mean precisely because it sounds more impressive. The median better reflects what a typical participant experienced.',25,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-data-studies-a-2','data','data:studies','data-studies-a-2','advanced','truefalse','True or false: An online poll where readers choose whether to respond can be safely generalized to the whole population.','True or false: An online poll where readers choose whether to respond can be safely generalized to the whole population.',ARRAY['True','False']::text[],ARRAY['True','False']::text[],1,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Self-selected respondents differ systematically from non-responders, producing self-selection bias.','Self-selected respondents differ systematically from non-responders, producing self-selection bias.','Voluntary-response or self-selected samples include only people motivated enough to participate, who often hold stronger or unusual opinions. This creates self-selection bias that distorts the results. Reliable generalization requires a randomly drawn, representative sample rather than whoever chooses to respond.','Voluntary-response or self-selected samples include only people motivated enough to participate, who often hold stronger or unusual opinions. This creates self-selection bias that distorts the results. Reliable generalization requires a randomly drawn, representative sample rather than whoever chooses to respond.',25,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bank-interpersonal-listening-1','interpersonal','interpersonal:listening','interpersonal-listening-1','beginner','mcq','A coworker is explaining a problem they ran into. Which behavior best shows you are actively listening?','A coworker is explaining a problem they ran into. Which behavior best shows you are actively listening?',ARRAY['Paraphrasing what they said back to them to confirm you understood','Thinking about how you''ll respond while they are still talking','Checking your phone but nodding occasionally','Jumping in to solve the problem before they finish']::text[],ARRAY['Paraphrasing what they said back to them to confirm you understood','Thinking about how you''ll respond while they are still talking','Checking your phone but nodding occasionally','Jumping in to solve the problem before they finish']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Paraphrasing the speaker''s point back to them confirms understanding and signals that you were genuinely attending to their words.','Paraphrasing the speaker''s point back to them confirms understanding and signals that you were genuinely attending to their words.','Active listening means fully concentrating on the speaker rather than passively hearing them. A core technique is reflecting or paraphrasing what you heard, which both checks your understanding and shows the speaker they were heard. This builds trust and reduces miscommunication.','Active listening means fully concentrating on the speaker rather than passively hearing them. A core technique is reflecting or paraphrasing what you heard, which both checks your understanding and shows the speaker they were heard. This builds trust and reduces miscommunication.',10,'approved','curated-taste');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bank-interpersonal-listening-2','interpersonal','interpersonal:listening','interpersonal-listening-2','intermediate','mcq','During a one-on-one, a teammate says, ''I guess the project went fine,'' but sounds flat and hesitant. What is the best active-listening response?','During a one-on-one, a teammate says, ''I guess the project went fine,'' but sounds flat and hesitant. What is the best active-listening response?',ARRAY['Reflect what you notice: ''You say it went fine, but you sound unsure. What''s on your mind?''','Take them at their word and move to the next agenda item','Reassure them: ''I''m sure it was great, don''t worry about it.''','Point out that they should sound more confident in meetings']::text[],ARRAY['Reflect what you notice: ''You say it went fine, but you sound unsure. What''s on your mind?''','Take them at their word and move to the next agenda item','Reassure them: ''I''m sure it was great, don''t worry about it.''','Point out that they should sound more confident in meetings']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Naming the mismatch between their words and tone invites them to share what they actually feel, which is the goal of listening for meaning beneath the words.','Naming the mismatch between their words and tone invites them to share what they actually feel, which is the goal of listening for meaning beneath the words.','Skilled listeners attend to nonverbal cues like tone, pace, and hesitation, not just the literal words. When words and signals conflict, gently reflecting the discrepancy opens space for the real message. This is sometimes called listening for the music behind the words.','Skilled listeners attend to nonverbal cues like tone, pace, and hesitation, not just the literal words. When words and signals conflict, gently reflecting the discrepancy opens space for the real message. This is sometimes called listening for the music behind the words.',15,'approved','curated-taste');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bank-interpersonal-listening-3','interpersonal','interpersonal:listening','interpersonal-listening-3','advanced','truefalse','True or False: Asking clarifying, open-ended questions can be a form of active listening, even though you are the one speaking.','True or False: Asking clarifying, open-ended questions can be a form of active listening, even though you are the one speaking.',ARRAY['True','False']::text[],ARRAY['True','False']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Open-ended questions that draw out and deepen the speaker''s meaning are a recognized active-listening skill, because their purpose is to understand rather than to redirect.','Open-ended questions that draw out and deepen the speaker''s meaning are a recognized active-listening skill, because their purpose is to understand rather than to redirect.','Active listening is not silent passivity; it includes verbal techniques that serve understanding. Open-ended questions such as ''What led you to that?'' encourage the speaker to elaborate and show you are tracking their thinking. The test is intent: questions that explore the speaker''s view aid listening, while questions that steer toward your own agenda do not.','Active listening is not silent passivity; it includes verbal techniques that serve understanding. Open-ended questions such as ''What led you to that?'' encourage the speaker to elaborate and show you are tracking their thinking. The test is intent: questions that explore the speaker''s view aid listening, while questions that steer toward your own agenda do not.',25,'approved','curated-taste');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bank-interpersonal-feedback-1','interpersonal','interpersonal:feedback','interpersonal-feedback-1','beginner','mcq','Which of these is the most effective feedback to give a colleague?','Which of these is the most effective feedback to give a colleague?',ARRAY['''In yesterday''s review, you interrupted Maria twice before she finished her point.''','''You''re kind of rude in meetings.''','''Everyone thinks you talk over people.''','''You always make meetings difficult.''']::text[],ARRAY['''In yesterday''s review, you interrupted Maria twice before she finished her point.''','''You''re kind of rude in meetings.''','''Everyone thinks you talk over people.''','''You always make meetings difficult.''']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Effective feedback describes a specific, observable behavior at a specific time, rather than labeling the person''s character.','Effective feedback describes a specific, observable behavior at a specific time, rather than labeling the person''s character.','Good feedback is specific and behavior-focused, pointing to what someone actually did rather than judging who they are. Vague or character-based labels like ''rude'' put people on the defensive and give them nothing concrete to change. Naming the exact behavior makes the feedback both fair and actionable.','Good feedback is specific and behavior-focused, pointing to what someone actually did rather than judging who they are. Vague or character-based labels like ''rude'' put people on the defensive and give them nothing concrete to change. Naming the exact behavior makes the feedback both fair and actionable.',10,'approved','curated-taste');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bank-interpersonal-feedback-2','interpersonal','interpersonal:feedback','interpersonal-feedback-2','intermediate','mcq','You want to tell a teammate that their late report delayed your work. Which phrasing is most constructive?','You want to tell a teammate that their late report delayed your work. Which phrasing is most constructive?',ARRAY['''When the report arrived a day late, I had to rush my part and felt stressed.''','''You made me miss my deadline because you''re never on time.''','''Why can''t you ever get things in when you say you will?''','''It''s fine, but try not to be late, I guess.''']::text[],ARRAY['''When the report arrived a day late, I had to rush my part and felt stressed.''','''You made me miss my deadline because you''re never on time.''','''Why can''t you ever get things in when you say you will?''','''It''s fine, but try not to be late, I guess.''']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'An ''I'' statement that links a specific behavior to its concrete impact and your own experience delivers the message without attacking the person.','An ''I'' statement that links a specific behavior to its concrete impact and your own experience delivers the message without attacking the person.','''I'' statements describe the situation, the effect on you, and how you felt, instead of accusing the other person with ''you'' blame. The structure ''When X happened, I experienced Y'' keeps the focus on impact rather than character. This lowers defensiveness and makes the listener more able to hear and act on the feedback.','''I'' statements describe the situation, the effect on you, and how you felt, instead of accusing the other person with ''you'' blame. The structure ''When X happened, I experienced Y'' keeps the focus on impact rather than character. This lowers defensiveness and makes the listener more able to hear and act on the feedback.',15,'approved','curated-taste');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bank-interpersonal-feedback-3','interpersonal','interpersonal:feedback','interpersonal-feedback-3','advanced','mcq','A direct report did excellent work but you also need to raise a real concern. What approach makes the feedback most credible?','A direct report did excellent work but you also need to raise a real concern. What approach makes the feedback most credible?',ARRAY['Give genuine, specific praise and the specific concern as separate, clearly stated messages','Sandwich the criticism between two compliments so it stings less','Skip the praise and lead straight into the criticism to save time','Soften the concern so much that it sounds optional']::text[],ARRAY['Give genuine, specific praise and the specific concern as separate, clearly stated messages','Sandwich the criticism between two compliments so it stings less','Skip the praise and lead straight into the criticism to save time','Soften the concern so much that it sounds optional']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Keeping praise and concern specific and distinct preserves the credibility of both, whereas burying criticism dilutes the message and can make praise feel manipulative.','Keeping praise and concern specific and distinct preserves the credibility of both, whereas burying criticism dilutes the message and can make praise feel manipulative.','The classic ''feedback sandwich'' often backfires because people learn to discount the praise as mere padding for bad news. Research and practice favor being clear and specific about both strengths and concerns, treating each as a real, standalone message. Honesty paired with specificity earns trust; manufactured softening erodes it.','The classic ''feedback sandwich'' often backfires because people learn to discount the praise as mere padding for bad news. Research and practice favor being clear and specific about both strengths and concerns, treating each as a real, standalone message. Honesty paired with specificity earns trust; manufactured softening erodes it.',25,'approved','curated-taste');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bank-interpersonal-negotiation-1','interpersonal','interpersonal:negotiation','interpersonal-negotiation-1','beginner','mcq','In a negotiation, what does it mean to focus on ''interests'' rather than ''positions''?','In a negotiation, what does it mean to focus on ''interests'' rather than ''positions''?',ARRAY['Looking at the underlying needs behind what each side is demanding','Sticking firmly to your opening demand no matter what','Caring only about the other side''s stated final offer','Splitting the difference as quickly as possible']::text[],ARRAY['Looking at the underlying needs behind what each side is demanding','Sticking firmly to your opening demand no matter what','Caring only about the other side''s stated final offer','Splitting the difference as quickly as possible']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Interests are the underlying needs and motivations driving a demand, and focusing on them opens up solutions a rigid position would hide.','Interests are the underlying needs and motivations driving a demand, and focusing on them opens up solutions a rigid position would hide.','A position is what someone says they want; an interest is why they want it. Two people arguing over a single orange may both get more if one needs the peel and the other the fruit. Identifying interests behind positions is a foundation of principled negotiation because it reveals options that satisfy both sides.','A position is what someone says they want; an interest is why they want it. Two people arguing over a single orange may both get more if one needs the peel and the other the fruit. Identifying interests behind positions is a foundation of principled negotiation because it reveals options that satisfy both sides.',10,'approved','curated-taste');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bank-interpersonal-negotiation-2','interpersonal','interpersonal:negotiation','interpersonal-negotiation-2','intermediate','mcq','You are negotiating a contract. What does knowing your BATNA give you?','You are negotiating a contract. What does knowing your BATNA give you?',ARRAY['A clear sense of your best alternative if no deal is reached, so you know when to walk away','A guarantee that the other side will accept your first offer','Permission to ignore the other party''s interests entirely','A rule that you must always accept any offer above your asking price']::text[],ARRAY['A clear sense of your best alternative if no deal is reached, so you know when to walk away','A guarantee that the other side will accept your first offer','Permission to ignore the other party''s interests entirely','A rule that you must always accept any offer above your asking price']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'BATNA stands for Best Alternative To a Negotiated Agreement, and knowing it tells you the point at which walking away beats accepting a poor deal.','BATNA stands for Best Alternative To a Negotiated Agreement, and knowing it tells you the point at which walking away beats accepting a poor deal.','Your BATNA is what you will do if this particular negotiation fails. It sets your walk-away point: you should not accept any deal worse than your best alternative. A strong, well-understood BATNA increases your leverage and protects you from being pressured into an agreement that leaves you worse off.','Your BATNA is what you will do if this particular negotiation fails. It sets your walk-away point: you should not accept any deal worse than your best alternative. A strong, well-understood BATNA increases your leverage and protects you from being pressured into an agreement that leaves you worse off.',15,'approved','curated-taste');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bank-interpersonal-negotiation-3','interpersonal','interpersonal:negotiation','interpersonal-negotiation-3','advanced','mcq','The other party opens with an aggressive, extreme number. What is the most effective response?','The other party opens with an aggressive, extreme number. What is the most effective response?',ARRAY['Avoid anchoring to it, refocus on objective criteria, and ask how they arrived at that figure','Immediately counter with an equally extreme number in the opposite direction','Accept a small concession from their number to keep things friendly','Walk out of the negotiation in protest of the tactic']::text[],ARRAY['Avoid anchoring to it, refocus on objective criteria, and ask how they arrived at that figure','Immediately counter with an equally extreme number in the opposite direction','Accept a small concession from their number to keep things friendly','Walk out of the negotiation in protest of the tactic']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Declining to treat the extreme figure as a reference point and steering toward objective standards neutralizes the anchor without escalating or conceding.','Declining to treat the extreme figure as a reference point and steering toward objective standards neutralizes the anchor without escalating or conceding.','An aggressive first offer is an anchoring tactic, exploiting our tendency to judge value relative to the first number we hear. The countermeasure is to refuse the anchor''s pull and insist on independent, objective criteria such as market rates or precedent. Asking the other side to justify their number also exposes weak reasoning and resets the conversation onto fairer ground.','An aggressive first offer is an anchoring tactic, exploiting our tendency to judge value relative to the first number we hear. The countermeasure is to refuse the anchor''s pull and insist on independent, objective criteria such as market rates or precedent. Asking the other side to justify their number also exposes weak reasoning and resets the conversation onto fairer ground.',25,'approved','curated-taste');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bank-interpersonal-conflict-1','interpersonal','interpersonal:conflict','interpersonal-conflict-1','beginner','mcq','A friend is visibly upset and venting about a hard day. What is the most empathetic first response?','A friend is visibly upset and venting about a hard day. What is the most empathetic first response?',ARRAY['''That sounds really frustrating. What happened?''','''Well, at least it wasn''t worse than my day.''','''You should just stop letting it bother you.''','''Here''s exactly what you need to do to fix it.''']::text[],ARRAY['''That sounds really frustrating. What happened?''','''Well, at least it wasn''t worse than my day.''','''You should just stop letting it bother you.''','''Here''s exactly what you need to do to fix it.''']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Acknowledging the person''s emotion and inviting them to say more shows empathy before any attempt to fix or compare.','Acknowledging the person''s emotion and inviting them to say more shows empathy before any attempt to fix or compare.','Empathy starts with recognizing and validating another person''s feelings rather than minimizing, comparing, or rushing to solutions. Acknowledging emotion first signals that the person matters and makes them feel understood. Only once someone feels heard are they usually ready to think about solutions.','Empathy starts with recognizing and validating another person''s feelings rather than minimizing, comparing, or rushing to solutions. Acknowledging emotion first signals that the person matters and makes them feel understood. Only once someone feels heard are they usually ready to think about solutions.',10,'approved','curated-taste');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bank-interpersonal-conflict-2','interpersonal','interpersonal:conflict','interpersonal-conflict-2','intermediate','truefalse','True or False: When someone comes to you angry about a problem, acknowledging their emotion before jumping to solutions usually makes the conversation go better.','True or False: When someone comes to you angry about a problem, acknowledging their emotion before jumping to solutions usually makes the conversation go better.',ARRAY['True','False']::text[],ARRAY['True','False']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Acknowledging the emotion first helps the person feel heard and calms the interaction, making them more open to problem-solving afterward.','Acknowledging the emotion first helps the person feel heard and calms the interaction, making them more open to problem-solving afterward.','Strong emotion narrows people''s capacity to reason and absorb solutions. Naming and validating the feeling, sometimes called affect labeling, helps reduce its intensity and signals respect. Once the person feels understood, the conversation can shift productively to addressing the underlying problem.','Strong emotion narrows people''s capacity to reason and absorb solutions. Naming and validating the feeling, sometimes called affect labeling, helps reduce its intensity and signals respect. Once the person feels understood, the conversation can shift productively to addressing the underlying problem.',15,'approved','curated-taste');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bank-interpersonal-conflict-3','interpersonal','interpersonal:conflict','interpersonal-conflict-3','advanced','mcq','Two team members are in a heated disagreement and each insists the other is wrong. As a neutral colleague, what is the most effective way to de-escalate?','Two team members are in a heated disagreement and each insists the other is wrong. As a neutral colleague, what is the most effective way to de-escalate?',ARRAY['Have each person restate the other''s view to the other''s satisfaction before debating solutions','Decide who is right based on who argues more forcefully','Tell them both to drop it and move on for now','Take the side of whoever you personally agree with']::text[],ARRAY['Have each person restate the other''s view to the other''s satisfaction before debating solutions','Decide who is right based on who argues more forcefully','Tell them both to drop it and move on for now','Take the side of whoever you personally agree with']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Requiring each person to accurately restate the other''s view ensures both feel understood and surfaces the real disagreement, which lowers defensiveness before solving the problem.','Requiring each person to accurately restate the other''s view ensures both feel understood and surfaces the real disagreement, which lowers defensiveness before solving the problem.','In heated conflict, people dig in partly because they feel unheard. A powerful de-escalation technique is to have each side reflect the other''s position until that person agrees it was captured fairly. This forces genuine perspective-taking, separates real disagreements from misunderstandings, and replaces a contest of wills with mutual understanding.','In heated conflict, people dig in partly because they feel unheard. A powerful de-escalation technique is to have each side reflect the other''s position until that person agrees it was captured fairly. This forces genuine perspective-taking, separates real disagreements from misunderstandings, and replaces a contest of wills with mutual understanding.',25,'approved','curated-taste');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-interpersonal-listening-b-1','interpersonal','interpersonal:listening','interpersonal-listening-b-1','beginner','mcq','A coworker is explaining a problem they''re facing. Which behavior best demonstrates active listening?','A coworker is explaining a problem they''re facing. Which behavior best demonstrates active listening?',ARRAY['Paraphrasing what they said to confirm you understood','Quickly offering a solution before they finish','Checking your phone while nodding occasionally','Changing the subject to a similar problem you once had']::text[],ARRAY['Paraphrasing what they said to confirm you understood','Quickly offering a solution before they finish','Checking your phone while nodding occasionally','Changing the subject to a similar problem you once had']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Paraphrasing shows the speaker you''ve genuinely processed their message and lets them correct any misunderstanding.','Paraphrasing shows the speaker you''ve genuinely processed their message and lets them correct any misunderstanding.','Active listening means fully concentrating on the speaker rather than just waiting to reply. A core technique is reflecting or paraphrasing the speaker''s words back to them. This confirms understanding and signals that you value what they said.','Active listening means fully concentrating on the speaker rather than just waiting to reply. A core technique is reflecting or paraphrasing the speaker''s words back to them. This confirms understanding and signals that you value what they said.',10,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-interpersonal-listening-b-2','interpersonal','interpersonal:listening','interpersonal-listening-b-2','beginner','truefalse','Interrupting someone to finish their sentence shows you''re engaged and listening well.','Interrupting someone to finish their sentence shows you''re engaged and listening well.',ARRAY['True','False']::text[],ARRAY['True','False']::text[],1,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Interrupting signals impatience and shifts focus to you rather than letting the speaker complete their own thought.','Interrupting signals impatience and shifts focus to you rather than letting the speaker complete their own thought.','Letting people finish their thoughts is a foundation of respectful listening. Interrupting, even with good intentions, can make speakers feel unheard or rushed. Allowing brief silences gives them space to express themselves fully.','Letting people finish their thoughts is a foundation of respectful listening. Interrupting, even with good intentions, can make speakers feel unheard or rushed. Allowing brief silences gives them space to express themselves fully.',10,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-interpersonal-listening-i-1','interpersonal','interpersonal:listening','interpersonal-listening-i-1','intermediate','mcq','A teammate says, ''I guess I''ll just handle the launch alone, like always.'' What''s the best active-listening response?','A teammate says, ''I guess I''ll just handle the launch alone, like always.'' What''s the best active-listening response?',ARRAY['It sounds like you''re feeling unsupported on this. Can you tell me more?','You''re not alone, stop exaggerating.','Okay, let me know if you need anything.','Everyone is busy, that''s just how launches go.']::text[],ARRAY['It sounds like you''re feeling unsupported on this. Can you tell me more?','You''re not alone, stop exaggerating.','Okay, let me know if you need anything.','Everyone is busy, that''s just how launches go.']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Reflecting the underlying feeling invites the speaker to share more and shows you heard the emotion behind the words.','Reflecting the underlying feeling invites the speaker to share more and shows you heard the emotion behind the words.','Active listening includes attending to the emotion beneath the literal words. Reflecting feelings (''it sounds like you''re feeling...'') validates the person and opens dialogue. This is more effective than dismissing, minimizing, or offering a quick fix.','Active listening includes attending to the emotion beneath the literal words. Reflecting feelings (''it sounds like you''re feeling...'') validates the person and opens dialogue. This is more effective than dismissing, minimizing, or offering a quick fix.',15,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-interpersonal-listening-i-2','interpersonal','interpersonal:listening','interpersonal-listening-i-2','intermediate','mcq','Which question type best encourages someone to elaborate during a conversation?','Which question type best encourages someone to elaborate during a conversation?',ARRAY['An open-ended question like ''What happened next?''','A closed yes/no question like ''Did that work?''','A leading question like ''You agree it was fine, right?''','A rapid series of short factual questions']::text[],ARRAY['An open-ended question like ''What happened next?''','A closed yes/no question like ''Did that work?''','A leading question like ''You agree it was fine, right?''','A rapid series of short factual questions']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Open-ended questions invite fuller responses and let the speaker steer the depth and direction of their answer.','Open-ended questions invite fuller responses and let the speaker steer the depth and direction of their answer.','Open-ended questions begin with words like what, how, or tell me, and cannot be answered with a single word. They encourage the speaker to elaborate and reveal more context. Closed and leading questions tend to shut down or steer the conversation.','Open-ended questions begin with words like what, how, or tell me, and cannot be answered with a single word. They encourage the speaker to elaborate and reveal more context. Closed and leading questions tend to shut down or steer the conversation.',15,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-interpersonal-listening-a-1','interpersonal','interpersonal:listening','interpersonal-listening-a-1','advanced','mcq','In a tense meeting, a stakeholder''s words say ''It''s fine'' but their tone is clipped and arms are crossed. What does skilled listening call for?','In a tense meeting, a stakeholder''s words say ''It''s fine'' but their tone is clipped and arms are crossed. What does skilled listening call for?',ARRAY['Gently naming the mismatch: ''You say it''s fine, but I sense some hesitation—what''s on your mind?''','Taking ''it''s fine'' at face value and moving on','Pointing out publicly that their body language is negative','Ignoring the cue to avoid making things awkward']::text[],ARRAY['Gently naming the mismatch: ''You say it''s fine, but I sense some hesitation—what''s on your mind?''','Taking ''it''s fine'' at face value and moving on','Pointing out publicly that their body language is negative','Ignoring the cue to avoid making things awkward']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Gently surfacing the gap between words and nonverbal cues invites honesty without putting the person on the defensive.','Gently surfacing the gap between words and nonverbal cues invites honesty without putting the person on the defensive.','When verbal and nonverbal messages conflict, the nonverbal signal often carries the truer feeling. Skilled listeners tactfully name the discrepancy to invite the real concern into the open. Doing this privately and curiously, rather than accusingly, preserves the person''s dignity.','When verbal and nonverbal messages conflict, the nonverbal signal often carries the truer feeling. Skilled listeners tactfully name the discrepancy to invite the real concern into the open. Doing this privately and curiously, rather than accusingly, preserves the person''s dignity.',25,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-interpersonal-listening-a-2','interpersonal','interpersonal:listening','interpersonal-listening-a-2','advanced','mcq','You notice you''re mentally rehearsing your rebuttal while a colleague is still talking. What''s the most effective self-correction?','You notice you''re mentally rehearsing your rebuttal while a colleague is still talking. What''s the most effective self-correction?',ARRAY['Refocus attention on understanding their point before forming any response','Interrupt now so you don''t forget your counterargument','Tune out and wait for them to finish so you can speak','Write down your rebuttal in detail as they talk']::text[],ARRAY['Refocus attention on understanding their point before forming any response','Interrupt now so you don''t forget your counterargument','Tune out and wait for them to finish so you can speak','Write down your rebuttal in detail as they talk']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Listening to understand rather than to reply is what makes comprehension and connection possible.','Listening to understand rather than to reply is what makes comprehension and connection possible.','A common barrier to listening is preparing your response instead of absorbing the other person''s message. This ''listening to reply'' splits your attention and causes you to miss meaning. The fix is to suspend your own agenda and prioritize understanding first.','A common barrier to listening is preparing your response instead of absorbing the other person''s message. This ''listening to reply'' splits your attention and causes you to miss meaning. The fix is to suspend your own agenda and prioritize understanding first.',25,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-interpersonal-feedback-b-1','interpersonal','interpersonal:feedback','interpersonal-feedback-b-1','beginner','mcq','Which feedback is most useful because it focuses on specific behavior?','Which feedback is most useful because it focuses on specific behavior?',ARRAY['In the meeting you interrupted Sam twice before he finished his point.','You''re kind of rude in meetings.','You have a bad attitude.','People don''t really like working with you.']::text[],ARRAY['In the meeting you interrupted Sam twice before he finished his point.','You''re kind of rude in meetings.','You have a bad attitude.','People don''t really like working with you.']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Naming the specific observable behavior makes the feedback clear and actionable rather than a vague character judgment.','Naming the specific observable behavior makes the feedback clear and actionable rather than a vague character judgment.','Effective feedback targets specific behaviors, not personality or character. Describing exactly what happened (''you interrupted twice'') gives the person something concrete to change. Vague labels like ''rude'' or ''bad attitude'' feel like attacks and offer no clear path forward.','Effective feedback targets specific behaviors, not personality or character. Describing exactly what happened (''you interrupted twice'') gives the person something concrete to change. Vague labels like ''rude'' or ''bad attitude'' feel like attacks and offer no clear path forward.',10,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-interpersonal-feedback-b-2','interpersonal','interpersonal:feedback','interpersonal-feedback-b-2','beginner','truefalse','Positive feedback should also be specific, not just a general ''good job.''','Positive feedback should also be specific, not just a general ''good job.''',ARRAY['True','False']::text[],ARRAY['True','False']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Specific praise tells the person exactly what to keep doing, making it more meaningful and reinforcing than a vague compliment.','Specific praise tells the person exactly what to keep doing, making it more meaningful and reinforcing than a vague compliment.','Feedback principles apply to praise as well as criticism. Specific positive feedback, such as naming the exact action that helped, reinforces the behavior you want repeated. A generic ''good job'' feels nice but gives little guidance on what to continue.','Feedback principles apply to praise as well as criticism. Specific positive feedback, such as naming the exact action that helped, reinforces the behavior you want repeated. A generic ''good job'' feels nice but gives little guidance on what to continue.',10,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-interpersonal-feedback-i-1','interpersonal','interpersonal:feedback','interpersonal-feedback-i-1','intermediate','mcq','A report missed a deadline. Which opener delivers the concern most constructively?','A report missed a deadline. Which opener delivers the concern most constructively?',ARRAY['When the report came in two days late, I had to delay the client update.','You always miss your deadlines.','Why can''t you ever get things in on time?','You made me look bad in front of the client.']::text[],ARRAY['When the report came in two days late, I had to delay the client update.','You always miss your deadlines.','Why can''t you ever get things in on time?','You made me look bad in front of the client.']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'An ''I'' statement tied to a specific event and its impact avoids blame while clearly communicating the consequence.','An ''I'' statement tied to a specific event and its impact avoids blame while clearly communicating the consequence.','''I'' statements describe the situation, your reaction, and the impact without accusing the other person. Phrasing like ''when X happened, the effect was Y'' keeps focus on facts and consequences. This reduces defensiveness compared with ''you'' accusations and absolutes like ''always.''','''I'' statements describe the situation, your reaction, and the impact without accusing the other person. Phrasing like ''when X happened, the effect was Y'' keeps focus on facts and consequences. This reduces defensiveness compared with ''you'' accusations and absolutes like ''always.''',15,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-interpersonal-feedback-i-2','interpersonal','interpersonal:feedback','interpersonal-feedback-i-2','intermediate','mcq','When is feedback generally most effective?','When is feedback generally most effective?',ARRAY['Soon after the event, in a private and appropriate setting','Saved up and delivered all at once in the annual review','Immediately, in front of the whole team for emphasis','Only when the person specifically asks for it']::text[],ARRAY['Soon after the event, in a private and appropriate setting','Saved up and delivered all at once in the annual review','Immediately, in front of the whole team for emphasis','Only when the person specifically asks for it']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Timely, private feedback lets the person recall and act on the specifics while protecting their dignity.','Timely, private feedback lets the person recall and act on the specifics while protecting their dignity.','Feedback works best when it is timely, given close enough to the event that details are fresh. Corrective feedback should typically be delivered privately to avoid embarrassment. Saving issues for a single annual review makes them harder to recall and to address.','Feedback works best when it is timely, given close enough to the event that details are fresh. Corrective feedback should typically be delivered privately to avoid embarrassment. Saving issues for a single annual review makes them harder to recall and to address.',15,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-interpersonal-feedback-a-1','interpersonal','interpersonal:feedback','interpersonal-feedback-a-1','advanced','mcq','A high performer reacts defensively to your corrective feedback. What''s the best next move?','A high performer reacts defensively to your corrective feedback. What''s the best next move?',ARRAY['Acknowledge their reaction and ask for their perspective on the situation','Repeat your point more firmly until they accept it','Drop the issue to keep the peace','Remind them of your authority to give the feedback']::text[],ARRAY['Acknowledge their reaction and ask for their perspective on the situation','Repeat your point more firmly until they accept it','Drop the issue to keep the peace','Remind them of your authority to give the feedback']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Inviting their perspective turns feedback into a two-way dialogue and lowers defensiveness so the message can land.','Inviting their perspective turns feedback into a two-way dialogue and lowers defensiveness so the message can land.','Feedback is most effective as a dialogue, not a verdict. When someone reacts defensively, acknowledging their emotion and seeking their view helps them feel respected and reduces threat. This collaborative stance increases the odds they will actually consider the feedback.','Feedback is most effective as a dialogue, not a verdict. When someone reacts defensively, acknowledging their emotion and seeking their view helps them feel respected and reduces threat. This collaborative stance increases the odds they will actually consider the feedback.',25,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-interpersonal-feedback-a-2','interpersonal','interpersonal:feedback','interpersonal-feedback-a-2','advanced','mcq','Why is the traditional ''praise-criticism-praise sandwich'' often criticized as a feedback method?','Why is the traditional ''praise-criticism-praise sandwich'' often criticized as a feedback method?',ARRAY['It can dilute the core message and make praise feel insincere','It is too direct and harsh for most people','It removes all positive feedback from the conversation','It only works in written form, never in person']::text[],ARRAY['It can dilute the core message and make praise feel insincere','It is too direct and harsh for most people','It removes all positive feedback from the conversation','It only works in written form, never in person']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Burying criticism between compliments can obscure the real point and train people to distrust your praise.','Burying criticism between compliments can obscure the real point and train people to distrust your praise.','The feedback sandwich aims to soften criticism but often backfires. Recipients may miss the actual concern or learn to brace whenever they hear praise, eroding its value. Clear, respectful, direct feedback that separates genuine praise from development points is usually more honest and effective.','The feedback sandwich aims to soften criticism but often backfires. Recipients may miss the actual concern or learn to brace whenever they hear praise, eroding its value. Clear, respectful, direct feedback that separates genuine praise from development points is usually more honest and effective.',25,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-interpersonal-negotiation-b-1','interpersonal','interpersonal:negotiation','interpersonal-negotiation-b-1','beginner','mcq','In negotiation, what is the difference between a position and an interest?','In negotiation, what is the difference between a position and an interest?',ARRAY['A position is what someone demands; an interest is the underlying need behind it','A position is flexible; an interest is fixed and non-negotiable','They mean the same thing in practice','A position is the other side''s need; an interest is your own demand']::text[],ARRAY['A position is what someone demands; an interest is the underlying need behind it','A position is flexible; an interest is fixed and non-negotiable','They mean the same thing in practice','A position is the other side''s need; an interest is your own demand']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Positions are the stated demands, while interests are the deeper motivations that often allow for creative solutions.','Positions are the stated demands, while interests are the deeper motivations that often allow for creative solutions.','A position is the specific thing a party says they want, such as a price or deadline. An interest is the underlying need or concern driving that demand. Focusing on interests rather than positions opens room for solutions that satisfy both sides.','A position is the specific thing a party says they want, such as a price or deadline. An interest is the underlying need or concern driving that demand. Focusing on interests rather than positions opens room for solutions that satisfy both sides.',10,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-interpersonal-negotiation-b-2','interpersonal','interpersonal:negotiation','interpersonal-negotiation-b-2','beginner','truefalse','Your BATNA is your best alternative to a negotiated agreement—what you''ll do if no deal is reached.','Your BATNA is your best alternative to a negotiated agreement—what you''ll do if no deal is reached.',ARRAY['True','False']::text[],ARRAY['True','False']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'BATNA stands for Best Alternative To a Negotiated Agreement and defines your fallback if the talk fails.','BATNA stands for Best Alternative To a Negotiated Agreement and defines your fallback if the talk fails.','BATNA is the course of action you''ll take if the negotiation produces no agreement. Knowing your BATNA tells you when to accept a deal and when to walk away. A strong BATNA gives you more leverage and confidence at the table.','BATNA is the course of action you''ll take if the negotiation produces no agreement. Knowing your BATNA tells you when to accept a deal and when to walk away. A strong BATNA gives you more leverage and confidence at the table.',10,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-interpersonal-negotiation-i-1','interpersonal','interpersonal:negotiation','interpersonal-negotiation-i-1','intermediate','mcq','Two teams both claim they need the single shared meeting room at 10 a.m. What''s the most interest-based approach?','Two teams both claim they need the single shared meeting room at 10 a.m. What''s the most interest-based approach?',ARRAY['Ask each team why they need that slot to find a solution that meets both needs','Give it to whoever asked first and tell the other to deal with it','Split the room in half so each gets part of it','Flip a coin to decide who gets the room']::text[],ARRAY['Ask each team why they need that slot to find a solution that meets both needs','Give it to whoever asked first and tell the other to deal with it','Split the room in half so each gets part of it','Flip a coin to decide who gets the room']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Exploring the reasons behind each demand can reveal options, like a different time or format, that satisfy both teams.','Exploring the reasons behind each demand can reveal options, like a different time or format, that satisfy both teams.','When positions clash, asking ''why'' uncovers the underlying interests. One team may need the room for a client call while the other just needs any quiet space. Understanding these differences often reveals a solution neither side saw from their stated positions.','When positions clash, asking ''why'' uncovers the underlying interests. One team may need the room for a client call while the other just needs any quiet space. Understanding these differences often reveals a solution neither side saw from their stated positions.',15,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-interpersonal-negotiation-i-2','interpersonal','interpersonal:negotiation','interpersonal-negotiation-i-2','intermediate','mcq','What does it mean to use objective criteria in a negotiation?','What does it mean to use objective criteria in a negotiation?',ARRAY['Grounding the deal in fair, independent standards like market rates or data','Insisting on whatever number you decided in advance','Letting the more senior person set all the terms','Splitting every difference exactly down the middle']::text[],ARRAY['Grounding the deal in fair, independent standards like market rates or data','Insisting on whatever number you decided in advance','Letting the more senior person set all the terms','Splitting every difference exactly down the middle']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Objective criteria let both parties measure fairness against an external standard instead of a contest of wills.','Objective criteria let both parties measure fairness against an external standard instead of a contest of wills.','Principled negotiation favors objective criteria such as market value, expert opinion, or precedent. Anchoring terms to independent standards makes outcomes feel fair and defensible. This shifts the discussion from a battle of stubbornness to a search for a legitimate benchmark.','Principled negotiation favors objective criteria such as market value, expert opinion, or precedent. Anchoring terms to independent standards makes outcomes feel fair and defensible. This shifts the discussion from a battle of stubbornness to a search for a legitimate benchmark.',15,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-interpersonal-negotiation-a-1','interpersonal','interpersonal:negotiation','interpersonal-negotiation-a-1','advanced','mcq','A counterpart opens with an extreme, aggressive demand to anchor the talk. What''s the strongest response?','A counterpart opens with an extreme, aggressive demand to anchor the talk. What''s the strongest response?',ARRAY['Refuse to treat the anchor as legitimate and re-anchor with your own well-justified standard','Immediately counter near their number to seem reasonable','Accept it to avoid conflict and preserve the relationship','Walk out of the negotiation entirely on principle']::text[],ARRAY['Refuse to treat the anchor as legitimate and re-anchor with your own well-justified standard','Immediately counter near their number to seem reasonable','Accept it to avoid conflict and preserve the relationship','Walk out of the negotiation entirely on principle']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Declining to engage with an extreme anchor and offering your own criteria-based number prevents the demand from skewing the deal.','Declining to engage with an extreme anchor and offering your own criteria-based number prevents the demand from skewing the deal.','Anchoring is a tactic where the first number strongly influences the final outcome. To counter an extreme anchor, you avoid negotiating off of it and instead introduce your own figure backed by objective criteria. This resets the frame around fairness rather than the other side''s extreme.','Anchoring is a tactic where the first number strongly influences the final outcome. To counter an extreme anchor, you avoid negotiating off of it and instead introduce your own figure backed by objective criteria. This resets the frame around fairness rather than the other side''s extreme.',25,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-interpersonal-negotiation-a-2','interpersonal','interpersonal:negotiation','interpersonal-negotiation-a-2','advanced','mcq','How can a negotiator create a more integrative (win-win) outcome rather than a purely distributive one?','How can a negotiator create a more integrative (win-win) outcome rather than a purely distributive one?',ARRAY['Identify differing priorities and trade across issues so each side gains on what matters most to them','Focus on claiming the largest possible share of a fixed pie','Hide all information so the other side can''t gain leverage','Make concessions only when threatened']::text[],ARRAY['Identify differing priorities and trade across issues so each side gains on what matters most to them','Focus on claiming the largest possible share of a fixed pie','Hide all information so the other side can''t gain leverage','Make concessions only when threatened']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Trading across issues that each side values differently expands the total value rather than just dividing a fixed amount.','Trading across issues that each side values differently expands the total value rather than just dividing a fixed amount.','Distributive negotiation treats value as a fixed pie to be divided, while integrative negotiation expands it. By sharing priorities and trading low-value-to-you items for high-value-to-you ones, both parties can gain. Logrolling across issues with different importance to each side is a key way to create joint value.','Distributive negotiation treats value as a fixed pie to be divided, while integrative negotiation expands it. By sharing priorities and trading low-value-to-you items for high-value-to-you ones, both parties can gain. Logrolling across issues with different importance to each side is a key way to create joint value.',25,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-interpersonal-conflict-b-1','interpersonal','interpersonal:conflict','interpersonal-conflict-b-1','beginner','mcq','A colleague comes to you visibly upset about a decision. What should you do first?','A colleague comes to you visibly upset about a decision. What should you do first?',ARRAY['Acknowledge their emotion before discussing the facts of the decision','Immediately explain why the decision was correct','Tell them not to take it personally','List all the reasons their reaction is an overreaction']::text[],ARRAY['Acknowledge their emotion before discussing the facts of the decision','Immediately explain why the decision was correct','Tell them not to take it personally','List all the reasons their reaction is an overreaction']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Acknowledging the emotion first helps the person feel heard and calms them enough to discuss the issue productively.','Acknowledging the emotion first helps the person feel heard and calms them enough to discuss the issue productively.','When someone is emotional, addressing the feeling comes before solving the problem. Acknowledging emotion (''I can see this really frustrated you'') helps the person feel understood. Only once they feel heard are they ready to engage with facts and solutions.','When someone is emotional, addressing the feeling comes before solving the problem. Acknowledging emotion (''I can see this really frustrated you'') helps the person feel understood. Only once they feel heard are they ready to engage with facts and solutions.',10,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-interpersonal-conflict-b-2','interpersonal','interpersonal:conflict','interpersonal-conflict-b-2','beginner','truefalse','Empathy means agreeing with the other person''s point of view.','Empathy means agreeing with the other person''s point of view.',ARRAY['True','False']::text[],ARRAY['True','False']::text[],1,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Empathy is understanding and acknowledging another''s feelings and perspective, which is distinct from agreeing with them.','Empathy is understanding and acknowledging another''s feelings and perspective, which is distinct from agreeing with them.','Empathy is the ability to understand and share the feelings of another person. You can empathize with someone''s frustration without agreeing that their conclusion is correct. Separating understanding from agreement lets you connect even during disagreement.','Empathy is the ability to understand and share the feelings of another person. You can empathize with someone''s frustration without agreeing that their conclusion is correct. Separating understanding from agreement lets you connect even during disagreement.',10,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-interpersonal-conflict-i-1','interpersonal','interpersonal:conflict','interpersonal-conflict-i-1','intermediate','mcq','Two teammates are in an escalating argument and both turn to you. What''s the most de-escalating move?','Two teammates are in an escalating argument and both turn to you. What''s the most de-escalating move?',ARRAY['Acknowledge both viewpoints and refocus on the shared goal they both care about','Side with whoever has the stronger argument','Tell them both to calm down and stop being dramatic','Leave them to sort it out so you stay neutral']::text[],ARRAY['Acknowledge both viewpoints and refocus on the shared goal they both care about','Side with whoever has the stronger argument','Tell them both to calm down and stop being dramatic','Leave them to sort it out so you stay neutral']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Validating both perspectives and reorienting toward a common goal lowers defensiveness and creates room for resolution.','Validating both perspectives and reorienting toward a common goal lowers defensiveness and creates room for resolution.','De-escalation often starts with making each party feel heard rather than picking a winner. Naming the common goal reminds both people they are on the same side. Telling people to ''calm down'' usually backfires by dismissing their feelings.','De-escalation often starts with making each party feel heard rather than picking a winner. Naming the common goal reminds both people they are on the same side. Telling people to ''calm down'' usually backfires by dismissing their feelings.',15,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-interpersonal-conflict-i-2','interpersonal','interpersonal:conflict','interpersonal-conflict-i-2','intermediate','mcq','Which statement best reflects empathy toward a frustrated customer?','Which statement best reflects empathy toward a frustrated customer?',ARRAY['I understand why this delay is frustrating—let''s figure out how to fix it.','There''s nothing I can do, it''s company policy.','Calm down, it''s really not a big deal.','Other customers don''t seem to have this problem.']::text[],ARRAY['I understand why this delay is frustrating—let''s figure out how to fix it.','There''s nothing I can do, it''s company policy.','Calm down, it''s really not a big deal.','Other customers don''t seem to have this problem.']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Naming and validating the customer''s frustration before moving to a solution shows genuine empathy and builds trust.','Naming and validating the customer''s frustration before moving to a solution shows genuine empathy and builds trust.','Empathic responses name the other person''s feeling and signal that it makes sense. This validation reduces defensiveness and shows you''re on their side. Dismissive replies that minimize or deflect tend to escalate frustration instead.','Empathic responses name the other person''s feeling and signal that it makes sense. This validation reduces defensiveness and shows you''re on their side. Dismissive replies that minimize or deflect tend to escalate frustration instead.',15,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-interpersonal-conflict-a-1','interpersonal','interpersonal:conflict','interpersonal-conflict-a-1','advanced','mcq','A long-running conflict persists because each side keeps restating its demands. What''s the most effective intervention?','A long-running conflict persists because each side keeps restating its demands. What''s the most effective intervention?',ARRAY['Shift the conversation from positions to the underlying interests and needs of each side','Have the more senior person simply decide the outcome','Encourage both sides to compromise halfway on every point','Avoid the topic until tensions cool on their own']::text[],ARRAY['Shift the conversation from positions to the underlying interests and needs of each side','Have the more senior person simply decide the outcome','Encourage both sides to compromise halfway on every point','Avoid the topic until tensions cool on their own']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Surfacing the underlying needs behind entrenched demands reveals common ground and options that repeated positions hide.','Surfacing the underlying needs behind entrenched demands reveals common ground and options that repeated positions hide.','Entrenched conflicts often stall because parties argue positions rather than interests. Reframing toward the needs and concerns beneath those positions opens space for creative, mutually acceptable solutions. This separates the people from the problem and turns adversaries into joint problem-solvers.','Entrenched conflicts often stall because parties argue positions rather than interests. Reframing toward the needs and concerns beneath those positions opens space for creative, mutually acceptable solutions. This separates the people from the problem and turns adversaries into joint problem-solvers.',25,'approved','curated-bank');
INSERT INTO "BankQuestion" ("id","skillId","subareaKey","concept","difficulty","type","questionEn","questionPl","optionsEn","optionsPl","correctIndex","acceptedAnswers","orderItems","correctOrder","explanationEn","explanationPl","theoryEn","theoryPl","xp","qualityState","model") VALUES ('bankq-interpersonal-conflict-a-2','interpersonal','interpersonal:conflict','interpersonal-conflict-a-2','advanced','mcq','You realize your own strong emotions are clouding your judgment during a heated disagreement. What''s the most emotionally intelligent response?','You realize your own strong emotions are clouding your judgment during a heated disagreement. What''s the most emotionally intelligent response?',ARRAY['Pause to name and regulate your own reaction before continuing the conversation','Push through and make your point while the emotion is strong','Blame the other person for provoking your reaction','Suppress the feeling entirely and pretend it isn''t there']::text[],ARRAY['Pause to name and regulate your own reaction before continuing the conversation','Push through and make your point while the emotion is strong','Blame the other person for provoking your reaction','Suppress the feeling entirely and pretend it isn''t there']::text[],0,ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::text[],ARRAY[]::int[],'Recognizing and regulating your own emotion first restores the clear thinking needed to handle the conflict constructively.','Recognizing and regulating your own emotion first restores the clear thinking needed to handle the conflict constructively.','Self-awareness and self-regulation are core to emotional intelligence in conflict. Noticing your own emotional state and taking a brief pause prevents reactive escalation. Naming a feeling to yourself helps tame it, restoring your ability to respond thoughtfully rather than react.','Self-awareness and self-regulation are core to emotional intelligence in conflict. Noticing your own emotional state and taking a brief pause prevents reactive escalation. Naming a feeling to yourself helps tame it, restoring your ability to respond thoughtfully rather than react.',25,'approved','curated-bank');
